title: monster bread
directions: Every great chef has that one specialty that he wants to share with the world.
Since the only other things I can do in the kitchen are make instant coffee and prepare hard-boiled eggs, I thought it important to share Breakfast By Byron.
I recommend serving this treat for those special weekends when you have time to pamper yourself.

title: hamburger with baked beans
directions: Cut the bacon in small pieces and add the chopped onion and saute.
Set aside.
Brown the hamburger and drain.
Mix bacon, hamburger, onions and rest of ingredients and pour into casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 9.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Add Salad Supreme seasoning to spaghetti.
Add dressing mix. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: no cook blueberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Spread over pie crusts.
Sprinkle pecans over cheese and sugar mixture. Spread pie filling over pecans. Top each pie with an 8 ounce container of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into popsicle molds and freeze.

title: guacamole
directions: Puree avocado and add all other ingredients.
Cool.

title: carrot cake supreme
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Mix together next five ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in carrots, bourbon and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until top springs back to the touch.
After semi-cool, remove from pan.
When totally cooled, cut cake exactly in half crosswise.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees.
Makes about 20 dozen cookies.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Mix as directed on package.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: cold lemon asparagus
directions: Wash and break off the woody base of the asparagus.
Tie into a bundle and steam upright in 1 1/2-inches of water.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until bright green and crunchy, not limp.
Rinse under cold water and drain.
Whisk the oil, lemon juice, mustard and honey in a bowl until emulsified.
Add salt and pepper.
Drizzle over the cold asparagus spears just before serving.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in medium cake baking pan.
Mix bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour into pan; add drained can of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, beat Crisco, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Gradually add flour, beating well. Stir in peanut butter chips. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheet to cool. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta noodles; drain.
Rinse in cool water.
In large bowl, combine cooked pasta, meat, vegetables and cheese.
Add dressing; toss lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, spread flat into two rectangles and press the seams together.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add the salad dressing and mix well.
Spread mixture on rectangles. Roll up, jelly roll style.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Slice thinly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: spinach dip in a bread bowl the easy way!!
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out the excess water.
Combine spinach, sour cream and party dip mix.
Stir in green onions and water chestnuts.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and put in a 13 x 9 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Bread crumbs may be sprinkled on top.

title: molded berry salad
directions: Place package of fruit in hot water to thaw for 10 minutes. Drain berries, reserving syrup.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted. Add lemonade concentrate; stir until melted.
Add the reserved syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in the drained berries and pecans.
Turn into a 6 cup ring mold.
Cover; chill in refrigerator for 6 to 24 hours.
Before serving, unmold onto a serving plate. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mammaw's white loaf cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar in a mixer.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk; beat 1 minute.
Add egg yolks, then vanilla and beat 3 to 4 minutes with mixer.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Add cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, until it springs back when touched.
Cool slightly, then remove from pan.
Dough will also make 3 layers.
Grease and flour pans and cover them with waxed paper, greased on both sides.
Bake at 350° until it springs back when touched.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Do not substitute salmon.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cook rice in 4 cups of boiling water.
Add salt to taste; set aside to cool.
Clean chicken thighs and remove skin.
Place in pan.
Salt to taste.
Add onion and green onions, as well as tomatoes.
Sprinkle with black pepper and hot sauce.
Add water and cook until well done.
Remove bones.
Add cooked mixed vegetables to chopped chicken; mix well and add to cooked rice. Toss well together with soy sauce.

title: red hot tomato salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add tomatoes and Tabasco sauce.
Pour mixture into a mold and refrigerate until congealed. Serve unmolded onto lettuce and with Horseradish Dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frostie mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges; reserve juice.
Add water to make 1 cup. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add all liquid.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted.
Chill 20 minutes or until thick.
Fold in oranges, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour into bowl or serving dishes.
Chill until set.
Garnish with oranges and/or mint leaves.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Divide mixture into 8 portions and shape into croquettes; roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Combine butter and paprika.
Drizzle over croquettes.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add pepper, onion, pineapple, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Shape in ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Chill 1 or 2 hours.
Garnish with fruit and serve with crackers.

title: nutty cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison into strips.
In a container combine the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Place meat in marinade overnight.
Turn if necessary.

title: rocky road sauce(use to top warm squares of any chocolate cake mix.)
directions: Combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup and butter in top of double boiler.
Stir in milk.
Cook over rapidly boiling water for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add marshmallows, almonds and vanilla.
Store leftover sauce in covered container in refrigerator.

title: peach and orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add ice cream and drained peaches. Let set a few minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: caribbean chicken
directions: Place chicken in large pot and add the next 6 ingredients. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove chicken from broth.
Reserve broth.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken on all sides and arrange in baking pan.
Add pineapple juice to broth; heat and pour over chicken.
Arrange pineapple chunks over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Lift chicken and pineapple chunks onto a serving dish and garnish with the remaining fruit.
If desired, thicken the gravy with several tablespoons of flour which have been blended with a little water; serve gravy separately. Number of Servings:

title: open faced peach pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour ingredients over sliced peaches and bake.

title: kavarma(bulgarian)
directions: Cut meat into small pieces and fry in oil and water.
Add the onions.
When tender, add sliced mushrooms, peppers, tomatoes, wine, savory, salt and parsley with a little water and mix.
Pour into earthenware dish or bowl.
Bake at 375F for 30-40 minutes.

title: shirley's salad
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, water and pineapple.
Add Jell-O.
Mix and let set until partially set.
Add cheese, Cool Whip, celery and walnuts.
Chill.

title: cottage cheese herb dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth and creamy.
Serve with raw vegetable sticks.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions into thin rings.
Saute in butter until limp or opaque.
Pour half of buttered onions into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half of Parmesan cheese and half of crumbled crackers.
Repeat layers, ending with layer of crumbled crackers and bake, uncovered, at 325° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball and refrigerate.
Top with chopped pecans.
Olives can be omitted, but it is important for the taste to put the onion in.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix ground beef, salt and onions in the warm water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is done.
Drain off water.
Add sugar, chili powder and catsup to beef.
Mix well. (May use white sugar.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat oleo, powdered sugar and oil.
Add vanilla, flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well and chill.
Roll into a small ball.
With end of thread spool, press out ball leaving a design. Bake on ungreased pan at 350°, about 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 to 9 dozen cookies.

title: apple nut cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir together the flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients with milk to egg mixture.
Stir all together.
Add apples, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: diet bread pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Mix together egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to milk.
Bread bread into small chunks in baking dish. Pour egg and milk mixture over bread, allowing a few pieces to float on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Set baking dish in pan of water to bake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with crumbs; use Rice Krispies or corn flakes.
Use 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour until firm.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onions. Add sour cream gradually, stirring occasionally.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in green beans; heat thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine Special-K and grated cheese; sprinkle over beans.
Bake in a moderately hot 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: tomato relish
directions: Soak tomatoes, onions, celery, green pepper and salt several hours or overnight.
Drain.
Put in large pot and add sugar, brown sugar, pickling spice and white vinegar.
Cook 30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Process 10 minutes.
Sugar, vinegar and spices can be boiling when adding vegetables.
Hot pepper can also be added.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; set aside.
Beat together the margarine and cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in cereal.
Add flour mixture; blend well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned around the edges.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain grease.
Add Dale's steak sauce and mushroom soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice, noodles or baked potatoes.

title: deep-dish chicken pie
directions: Combine soup and 1/2 cup milk in baking dish.
Add chicken, peas, pepper and onion.
Combine baking mix and 1/3 cup milk in bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together. Place in a heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310°. Remove from heat. When boiling ceases, stir in flavoring and coloring. Pour mixture into buttered cookie sheet. The mixture will get hard, break into pieces. (I cover a hammer with a plastic bag to break into pieces.) Put into an airtight container and sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook for 4 more minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from microwave.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir rapidly.
Spoon out rapidly onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Knead margarine, powdered sugar and peanut butter together until well blended. Roll into balls. Melt Hershey bars and paraffin in double boiler over hot, not boiling, water. Dip peanut butter balls in melted chocolate. Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: orange eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a blender.
Blend until mixture is thoroughly blended and foamy.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture alternating with the milk.
Add molasses and last the bananas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade strawberries
directions: Mix all except sugars and chill overnight.
Next day, shape like strawberries and roll in colored sugars.

title: chicken and gravy in the crock-pot
directions: Mix all ingredients with salt and pepper to taste on fillets. Cook all day in crock-pot.
Serve over rice.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cream some potatoes; set aside.
In skillet, brown ground beef with onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain meat.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with creamed potatoes, then add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: julio's chili con queso
directions: Cube both cheeses.
Place in a microwave-safe bowl, add soup. Fill soup can about 3/4 full with milk.
Pour over cheeses. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Microwave again until cheese is melted, approximately 4 to 5 minutes.
Use as a sauce or dip.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: chili-burgers
directions: In bowl, combine beef with next 7 ingredients; mix well. Shape mixture into 4 patties.
Broil on rack 6-inches from source of heat, about 5 minutes on each side, or until done to taste. Top each burger with 2 tablespoons yogurt and garnish with cilantro or parsley.

title: tomato chili
directions: Mix and cook slowly until thick. Can in jars. Use the water-bath method of processing.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix flour and spices.
Add flour and buttermilk mixture alternately to egg mixture.
Pour in cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: beef short ribs with raisin sauce
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces.
Brown in hot fat.
Pour off drippings. Season ribs with salt and pepper.
Add onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over ribs.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for about 2 hours or until meat is tender. Thicken sauce, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Break up and stir in Rice's chili.
Add catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, stirring occasionally.
Mixture will be thick.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch strips.
Cook bacon, onion rings and green pepper until vegetables are tender; drain.
Combine bacon, onion, green pepper, baked beans and barbecue sauce in a 2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with additional cooked bacon strips, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: very delicious deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs at least one hour, drain and then run cold water over to cool.
Remove shell, cut each egg in half and place yolks in bowl.
Add Miracle Whip
and mustard to egg yolks.
Whip well until mixture is almost smooth.
Place mixture back into eggs, garnish with paprika.
Let chill overnight.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk, apple and butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
For each pancake, pour about 1/3 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle. Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Cut cheese in 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook broccoli several minutes.
Place all ingredients into large mixing bowl and stir until mixed or blend in blender.
Pour into 2-quart dish and bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blueberry torte cake(three layer cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 3 round cake pans and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion, parsley, chopped egg whites, pimientos and dill weed.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and mix well. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Salad can be prepared a day ahead.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: strawberry delight dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/2 of the vanilla crumbs (crushed); spread with butter, egg and sugar mixture (put on in small gobs) then spread.
Slice strawberries onto mixture.
Then spread on whipped cream and the remaining cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
(Will keep leftovers after, covered for a day or two.)

title: no bake pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy and add milk and whip again. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Slice 3 bananas in graham cracker pie crust shell (see following), then pour in filling.
You can put a can of blueberry pie filling mix or cherry pie filling mix on top of the cream cheese mixture, then dip the other sliced banana in lemon juice and decorate the top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pina colada mousse
directions: In a saucepan combine gelatin and 1 cup juice.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in crushed pineapple and cream of coconut.
Stir in rum.
Chill until mixture mounds when stirred.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into a 2-quart freezer container or souffle dish.
Freeze until hard, then decorate with pineapple slices.
Cover and freeze until ready to serve.
Place in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving to make it easier to spoon.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
In pot you cooked it in, put softened cream cheese and cream of celery soup.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Mix spinach, saltines, cheese and soup mixture.
Put into casserole.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until heated thoroughly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients (except zucchini) together.
Add zucchini. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch (greased) pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together to make crumbs.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumbs for top.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine pulp, eggs, sugar, melted butter and milk.
Thoroughly mix flour and other dry ingredients and combine with pulp mixture. Pour into greased loaf pan or large baking bowl.
Bake at 325° for one hour, stirring often.
Serve warm or chilled, topped with whipped cream.

title: date bread (mom's)
directions: Pour boiling water over nuts and dates.
Add soda and cool. Mix other ingredients together.
Add nuts and date mixture when cool.
Grease two small loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Watch.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes and garlic with cold salted water.
Bring to boil, partly covered.
Cook 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove potatoes and garlic; boil the water until it is reduced to 1 cup. Peel potatoes and garlic (mash or rice) and whisk in enough potato water to bring potatoes to a thick creamy consistency.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Heat the olive oil.
At the table, drizzle desired amount over each portion.
Serves 4.

title: perfect roast
directions: Place long sheet of wide foil in a baking pan.
You need enough foil to seal the meat in.
Place roast on foil.
Pour in mushroom soup; sprinkle on onion soup mix.
Fold foil over from sides and crimp edges, then fold ends to seal.
Bake at 250° for 7 hours.
Do not open and peek.
Roast will make its own perfect gravy.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: Blend corn syrup, butter, peppermint and salt.
Add sugar. Mix until smooth.
Knead food coloring in.
Shape into small balls.
Flatten with fork on wax paper that's lining baking sheet. Let dry.
Makes 72.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread.
Dump pie filling.
Spread.
Dump dry cake mix.
Spread.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put slices of butter on top.
Bake for 48 to 53 minutes.
Fast, easy and delicious!

title: turkey macaroni pizza
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown turkey, onion and green pepper until veggies are tender.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
In medium bowl combine egg and milk.
Add macaroni and mix well.

title: melinda's tater tot casserole
directions: Mix both cans of soup with milk.
Mix with Tots, cheese and hamburger in pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serve after letting it set for 10 minutes out of oven.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water with sugar.
Mix milk, margarine, sugar and salt in a microwave bowl and warm until sugar is dissolved and margarine is melted.
Cool to lukewarm and add vanilla.
Meanwhile, beat egg in mixing bowl, add yeast mixture and milk mixture.
Add enough flour for a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Pour out on well floured board or counter.
Knead lightly.
Roll out dough to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cover with filling.
Pecans and/or raisins may be added if you choose. Roll up dough, jellyroll fashion, and slice about 3/4-inch thick, place on greased baking pan and let rise until double in size.
Bake in 450° oven on lower rack of oven for 10 minutes.
Glaze while hot.

title: glazed pineapple scones
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening. Beat egg and pineapple juice; add to flour mixture.
Add pineapple to mix only until flour is well moistened.
Drop batter on greased baking sheet, shaping into narrow bars.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost at once with Lemon Icing.

title: old-fashioned molasses cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Combine butter, sugar, molasses and eggs and blend well.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add boiling water and stir until smooth. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in large loaf pan.
Frost as desired.

title: baked hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole; sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Take skin off chicken breasts; turn breasts over in bowl of bread crumbs.
Use a large roasting pan with a small amount of oil on bottom of pan.
Set in chicken.
Drain cans of potatoes; scatter between chicken.
Put seasonings (sprinkle) over top. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
In the last 15 minutes, add onions to cook.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook whole zucchini in salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center, leaving 1/4-inch shell. Chop center portion and set aside.
Melt butter in large saucepan. Saute mushrooms about 3 minutes.
Add flour and oregano; remove from heat.
Stir in Monterey Jack cheese and pimentos.
Stir in reserved zucchini.
Fill zucchini with mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: italian tortellini soup
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add garlic and cook until lightly brown.
Slowly add chicken broth and tortellini.
Bring to boil; slow cook 10 minutes.
Add chopped spinach and stewed tomatoes. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls; garnish with Mozzarella cheese and pepper.
Bon appetit!

title: wild rice soup
directions: With butter, cook and stir celery, carrots, onions and green pepper in saucepan until celery is tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in wild rice, water and broth; heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes; stir occasionally. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat just until hot (do not boil).

title: old-fashioned potato soup
directions: Place
potatoes,
celery,
onions and water in saucepan over medium heat and cook until tender.
To 1/4 cup flour add a
little cold
water and stir until all lumps are dissolved. Add
salt and
pepper
and
milk.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, until thickened, stirring
to keep from sticking.
Add butter.
Eat with crackers or your favorite bread.

title: cherry picnic
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Place pineapple in bottom of casserole pan.
Layer cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Top with dry cake mix.
Add coconut over cake mix.
Add chopped nuts. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until syrup from pie filling bubbles to the top.
Best when served hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: olive potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add margarine, milk and olives.
Add more milk or margarine for the mashed potato consistency you like.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, heat 3/4-inch salad oil to 325° on deep-fat thermometer (or heat in electric skillet set at 325°).
Meanwhile, in bowl, with fork, mix flour with next 5 ingredients.
Holding a narrow-spouted funnel, close spout with finger; pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Over hot oil, carefully remove finger to let batter run out in a stream, while making a spiral about 6 inches in diameter.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden, turning once with tongs.
Repeat with remaining batter, stirring well before pouring.
Sprinkle funnel cakes lightly with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 7 funnel cakes.

title: waldorf wonder salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill briefly. Waldorf salad is in its original form as listed.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Bake in greased pans in 350° oven about 15 minutes.

title: savory spaghetti sauce
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve over spaghetti.
Yield:
1 quart.

title: ham and cheese roll
directions: Unroll pizza roll on lightly floured surface.
Roll until about 1/16-inch thick.
Spread on mustard-yogurt mixture. Sprinkle on caraway seed.
Lay slices of ham on dough, then sprinkle grated cheese.
Roll up towards self.
Pinch ends and place seam side down in a U shape on aluminum foil sprayed with Pam.
Cut through top layer about 1/4 inch to divide into 10 slices.
Beat egg with 1 tablespoon of water and brush over roll. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add all ingredients in bowl.
Toss until potatoes are evenly coated.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake, stirring once in a while.
Cook 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with parsley.

title: easy italian beef
directions: Cook chuck roast until it pulls apart and shreds.
In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Simmer over medium heat for 1 hour. Serve on sub buns with Mozzarella cheese and pepperocinis on the side.

title: swiss style green beans
directions: Make sauce for first seven ingredients and cook until thick. Add to green beans.
Place in greased casserole and cover with cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter, add corn flakes and sprinkle on top of bean mixture.
Cook at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread sour cream on top of beans.
Sprinkle olives over sour cream.
Sprinkle jalapeno peppers over sour cream.
Sprinkle chopped tomatoes over peppers.
Grate cheese over top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crescent italiano bake
directions: In skillet, brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish; sprinkle with grated cheese. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Combine sour cream and herbs; spread on top of meat mixture.
Top with crescent dough.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until dough is golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southwest cheesecake
directions: Mix 1 cup sour cream, Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, taco seasoning and chilies.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Blend well.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake until firm, 50 to 55 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Spread with 1 cup sour cream.
Return to oven 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Put in refrigerator and just before serving, put 3/4 cup salsa on top. Serve with taco chips or crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Stir in crushed crackers.
Mix together until crackers are coated.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add soups, sour cream and water chestnuts to chicken.
Stir together.
Pour half of crackers into casserole. Add chicken mixture.
Top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: tommie's and judy's pork chops casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix rice, water, mushroom soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with bell pepper slices and pork chops.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pork chops are done and rice is done.
Trim chops of all fat.
Can substitute soup with cream of chicken and substitute chicken for pork chops.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: my baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry.
When fairly crisp, add diced onion and fry with beans.
Cover and simmer until onions are transparent.
Mix rest of the nine ingredients well in bowl.
Add bacon/onion and all liquids.
Mix again.
Put in baking dish in 350° oven and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: saltine candy
directions: Boil the milk and sugar for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the other ingredients; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork, crisscross fashion.
Bake 7 to 11 minutes.

title: cheesy burritos
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up.
Chill to set.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Serve with picante sauce. Makes lots!

title: taco casserole
directions: Saute onion and hamburger.
Put in beans and tomato sauce. Heat and mix seasoning and simmer.
Have corn chips crushed in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
I use rolling pin to crush chips while still in bag, poke with pin to let air out.
Pour mixture over corn chips.
Have cheese grated.
Sprinkle over top of mix.
Let stand a few minutes, then shred lettuce over top and dice tomatoes in chunks over lettuce.
Serve while hot.

title: perfect roast beef(easy)
directions: Preheat the
oven to 375°.
Salt and pepper the roast which should be at room temperature.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and sour cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dinner casserole
directions: Day before:
In large skillet, saute beef, onion, chili powder, salt and pepper in butter or margarine until beef loses red color. Meanwhile, cook macaroni; drain.
In a 3-quart casserole, place beef and cooked macaroni.
Stir in kidney beans, tomatoes and undiluted tomato soup.
Cover and refrigerate.
About 1 hour and 30 minutes before serving, heat oven to 400°.
Bake casserole, covered, 1 hour and 10 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant fans
directions: Split eggplant lengthwise.
Place the halves, split side down, on a chopping board.
Cut each half lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices, leaving the slices attached at the end to form fans.
Slip tomato slices into the slits of the eggplant halves.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Cook hot sausage and drain.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer as follows: 1) Smear cream cheese over bottom of dish.
2) Hot sausage.
3) Green pepper and onion.
4) Salsa.
Grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with crackers.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meat with onion, ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar. Drain butter beans and kidney beans.
Add altogether and put in bean pot at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large kettle or bowl, mix together the cucumbers (do not peel), onions and pickling salt.
Pour 1 quart ice over and cover with a weighted lid.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Put pickles in large canner.
Add sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar.
Mix together well.
Bring this to a boil.
Fill quart canning jars (pints, if prefer) to the top of the jar with mixture.
Clean off top of jar.
Place lid and ring on.
Tighten down.
Set on cupboard to cool, covering jars with a towel.
Makes 7 pints.

title: meeting street pastry cups
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, salt and butter with a pastry blender.
Add eggs and incorporate them well, using your hands.
Form the dough into a ball, wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°. Pinch off the dough in small amounts and press into miniature muffin tins or pastry molds.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Fill with your favorite filling.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Mix beef with salt and pepper.
Shape into 18 meat balls.
Melt oleo in Dutch oven and brown meat balls on all sides.
Remove meat balls from Dutch oven and set aside.
Add onions and mushrooms to drippings in pan and stir in flour, lemon juice, catsup and bouillon.
Cook, stirring frequently until thickened.
Return meat balls to Dutch oven.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat until warm.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Turn crock-pot on low.
Melt margarine in bottom.
Mix all other ingredients with only half of sharp cheese.
Pour rest of cheese on top.
Cook for 3 hours on low.
Taste like you made it in an oven.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute all vegetables in margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well (add rice last).
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in large casserole dish at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
Recipe may be divided and 1/2 frozen for later use.

title: pecan sweet potatoes("fit for a king")
directions: Mix together and pour into greased dish.
I use electric mixer.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts in small pieces and mix with Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in airtight container.
Put 2 to 3 teaspoons in cup of boiling water.

title: peanut butter candy *
directions: Mix white sugar, syrup, milk and salt and cook over high heat until mixture forms a soft ball in water.
Let cool until the pan is cool, then stir in one half cup of crunchy peanut butter.
Pour into buttered dish and cut into squares.

title: two egg cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice about 3/8-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Put in a covered bowl; cover with ice water.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to fry.
Combine egg, salt, baking powder, water, flour, 1 tablespoon oil, lemon juice and pepper; stir until smooth.
Heat oil to 375°.
Remove onions from water and dip into batter.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: no bake chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Combine milk, sugar and cocoa in a heavy pan.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add oats and mix.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Let cool until stiff.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons. Excellent for children's parties or clubs.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and pepper.
Combine all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate fudge pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs with an electric beater, turn beater to medium and add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour half over chicken in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve remaining sauce over chicken while eating.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Combine first four ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Grease the bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely before slicing.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Combine potatoes and butter in medium bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients, use 1/2 gallon of sweet milk or enough for mixture to equal 1 gallon.
Place in ice cream freezer canister. Pack freezer with ice and rock salt.
Crank until handle is difficult to turn or until electric freezer stops.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese with hands.
Add Bisquick slowly and knead with hands.
Form balls on baking dish.
Put in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put toothpicks in each roll and serve.

title: butter cake
directions: Add all ingredients. Beat in 1 egg at a time. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and add enough water to make 2 cups. Boil juice; pour over jello, stirring until dissolved.
Add Cokes.
Chill until mixture thickens.
Add drained cherries, nuts and pineapple and chill until set.

title: orange creamsicles
directions: You will also need 12 (5-ounce) paper cups and 12 wooden sticks.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add next 7 ingredients; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese and cooked rice.
Layer rice mixture and meat mixture in a greased 6-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix flour with 1/2 water to form paste.
Add the rest of the water and cook over low heat until thick and clear; stirring constantly, cool.
Add glycerine and Borax.
If needed thin with water.
Divide and pour into small jars.
Add food coloring or poster paints to color.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together. Shape into patties and fry. Make sure batter is thick.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add onion, jalapeno and garlic to beef and saute for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, soups, seasonings and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add tortillas and cook 15 minutes more.
Garnish with cheese.
Enjoy!

title: sweet n sour meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into very small balls.
Fry in about 1 inch of oil, stirring frequently until lightly browned. Take up with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Transfer to a large, electric roaster.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add water to broth to make 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Combine cornbread, broth, eggs, celery, melted butter, stuffing mix and sage.
The secret to good dressing is to have enough broth.
Add 1 or 2 cans of canned broth if desired, to make it soupy and pourable.
Cook 30 minutes at 400°, until it starts to brown.
Do not overcook or it will be too dry.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
In a large bowl, mix pineapple, strawberries, nuts, bananas and Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into large 2-inch deep container.
Freeze.
Slice and serve.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Put dates, sugar and egg in skillet and stir until it lets go of skillet.
Take off heat and stir in Rice Krispies, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Stir until thick.
Butter hands and roll into balls.
Roll balls in coconut.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put drained green beans into ungreased casserole dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until mixture is heated to the bubbly stage.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Return to oven for 15 minutes at 300°.

title: shrimp yummy
directions: Crumble shrimp on bottom of greased flat casserole (souffle dish works well).
Cover with layer of grated eggs.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and chopped onions until fluffy.
Smear over eggs and shrimp.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased, floured pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fiesta cheese casserole
directions: Combine tortilla chips and oleo; press onto bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes; cool on wire rack. Beat the cream cheese at medium with electric mixer for
3 minutes or until fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Stir in cheese, chilies and ground red pepper.

Pour into prepared pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack. Place on a bed of fresh cilantro or parsley, if desired. Gently run a knife around edge of pan to release sides and let cool completely. Spread sour cream over top. Cover and chill. Arrange chopped peppers and remaining ingredients on top.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: impromptu stew
directions: Saute onion and pepper. Add beef and brown; drain grease.
Add mushrooms, seasoning and tomatoes.
Drain pasta; put back in pan with milk and cheese soup.
Add meat and tomato mixture.
Add vegetables; mix well.
Serve with buttered bread and salad.

title: vodka-barbecued chicken and ribs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine garlic, onion, ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, vodka, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken and ribs with garlic salt and pepper.
Place on grill.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.
During last 20 minutes of cooking, baste generously with sauce, turning frequently.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "three" chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add boiling water.
Beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured 13 x 11-inch pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Chop corn in blender.
Pour into bowl.
Add butter, whipping cream and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients; add to corn mixture.
Pour into long greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for
45 minutes to 1 hour (toothpick should come out clean).

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, oleo, eggs, vanilla and salt. Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in 9-inch pie pan or small loaf pan, 7 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with wooden toothpick for doneness.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter with hands until crumbly. Measure out 1 cup and save for topping.
Now mix egg, milk, soda and vanilla.
Add to first mixture; it will not be a smooth dough. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix reserved crumb mixture with nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Roll out graham crackers to crumbs. Add oleo and 1/2 cup sugar.
Make crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan and save some to sprinkle for garnish.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup water.
Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Beat Pet milk until rather fluffy. Add dissolved jello to cream cheese and mix. Fold into milk. Chill overnight.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in a 9 1/2-inch pie pan (glass seems to work best).
Add mixture to pan and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Squeeze lemon juice generously over the pancake and then sprinkle powdered sugar over it.
Serve hot.
Scrumptious with fresh fruit on top.

title: hacienda dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa and salt until well blended.
Spread cheese mixture in microwave pie plate or bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring every 2 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot buttered rum mix(yields about 25 cups)
directions: Combine butter, sugar and spices; beat until light and fluffy. Add ice cream; stir until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart freezer container; freeze.
To serve, thaw slightly.
Place 3 tablespoons mixture and 1 jigger dark rum into a large mug; fill with boiling water, stirring well.
Top with whipped cream and serve with cinnamon stick.

title: melbourne chicken
directions: Shake mixture of flour, curry powder and salt with chicken. Brown chicken in a little oil in skillet.
Place in baking dish. Stir sugar, beef cubes, onion, water, apricots, lemon juice and soy sauce in skillet.
Heat to boiling point, being sure to crush bouillon cubes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ranch chicken mac and cheese
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package. Stir in chicken, dressing, tomato and onions. Heat thoroughly. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles separately; drain.
Saute green pepper and onion in small amount of oil in large skillet, about 10 minutes.
Add soups and corn.
Mix well.
Next, add drained noodles and cheese.

title: savannah fried chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Place chicken in a shallow pan and pour buttermilk mixture over top; refrigerate at least 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Dredge chicken in flour.

Heat 1/2-inch of oil in a skillet to 350°; add chicken and cook, turning frequently, until chicken is brown on all sides. Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 25 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning occasionally.
Drain well on paper towels. Yield:
4 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Mix sugar and cheese together, then sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake according to directions.
Spread half of cake mixture in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt over medium heat, caramels, milk and margarine. Spread this mixture over cake.
Sprinkle over mixture 1 cup nuts and the chocolate chips.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes; drain.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Put beef over chicken.
Pour soup mixture over top and bake 30 more minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add Bisquick mix.
Mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
(Do not overbake.) Before cooling, press Kisses into center of cookie.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar with your hands until very soft and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, soda, flour and flavoring.
Mix well.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 inch square baking dish or pan.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk and butter.
Blend in nuts.
Spread in greased dish.
Sprinkle cocoa (1/4 cup) and brown sugar over butter in pan.
Pour hot tap water over entire batter. Bake 35 or 40 minutes or until batter is set and sauce bubbles. Let cool before slicing.
It makes it's own chocolate sauce.
Good with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening and beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring and lemon juice.
Beat until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: crock pot apple butter
directions: Core and chop apples, do not peel.
Combine apples and cider in crock pot.
Cover and cook on low for 10 - 12 hours or until apples are mushy.
Puree in food mill.
Return apples to crock pot, add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook uncovered until thickened.
Can to freeze.
Makes 8 cups.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spread in an ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Yields 64 squares.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Cut pears in bite size and pineapple.
Mix all well.
Let chill at least 12 hours.
Best if 24 hours.

title: baked tuna
directions: Mix and pour into a greased pan and bake in slow oven 325 degrees for 70 minutes.

title: butterscotch pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan on medium heat.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pecans.
Cook over low heat.
When mixture boils, cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Beat until thickened.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased wax paper.
Makes 24 to 28 pieces.

title: mom's yorkshire pudding(serves 6)
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a large bowl.

Lightly beat the egg in another bowl and stir in the milk and water with a fork. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and gradually pour in the liquid, whisking just until the batter is smooth.
Let the batter rest for 1 hour.
Heat the oven to 425°.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Combine beans, olive oil and 1/3 cup bean liquid in a 2-quart microwave bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Heat at 100% (High) for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven and mash bean mixture with fork until smooth.
Stir in cheese, onion, chili powder and paprika.
Cover and heat for approximately 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and serve warm.

title: five minute buttered crunch
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine and stir in salt.
Add Chex, stirring until well coated.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese, stirring until Chex are well coated.
Spread on paper towel; makes about 6 cups.

title: marvelous mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop enough stems to make 1/2 cup.
Saute mushroom caps in butter (turning once) for 5 minutes. In bowl, combine both cheeses, onion and chopped stems.
Mix well. Fill mushroom caps and broil until golden brown.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: ham quiche
directions: Beat eggs and half and half and add flour.
Place Swiss cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle mushrooms over cheese, then ham. Pour egg/cream mixture over other items in pie shell.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, meat, onion and soup sauce.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: african chop
directions: Cut up chicken and fry in oil with salt and pepper.
Put onion and tomatoes in blender 1 minute.
Add to chicken and cook 5 minutes.
Mix flour and water and add to chicken stew.
Cook until tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Then add (as desired) last 7 ingredients set out for people to add to rice and stew.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: saltine cracker fudge
directions: Note:
This recipe was used during World War II frequently.

title: polly's cornbread dressing
directions: Cut up whole chicken and cook in pressure cooker approximately 15 minutes. Remove chicken pieces form liquid, reserving the broth. Debone cooled chicken piece, then chop with knife. Mix up cornbread mixture, enough to make 2 skillets (1 large and 1 medium) of cornbread. Cook. Cool. Crumble. Chop large onion and celery (can also add chopped green onions). Melt butter and saut chopped onions and celery. Beat eggs. Crumble white loaf bread.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter, powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in 8 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan.

title: waffle whoopie pie
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in bowl and mix with spoon.
Then add soda and boiling water.
Cook at 375° to 400°; depends on waffle iron.
Spray after each time.
Fill with filling.

title: souper burger
directions: Fry ground beef and onion in the shortening, drain.
Add tomato soup, mustard and dash of pepper.
Mix together and put on toasted buns and serve.

title: crunchy beans and wiener casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with onion rings and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Preheat
oven to 250°. Mix all ingredients except nuts. Dip nuts
into mixture and place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Cool and store in airtight container until serving time.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Boil pineapple, sugar and lemon juice together 5 minutes; cool. Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Mix and add all remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and microwave for 10 minutes covered with plastic wrap.
Unwrap and put in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Squeeze some butter on potatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour ranch dressing over potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese, then bacon bits.
Cover with foil and cook 45 minutes in 400 degree oven.
Remove foil and put on top shelf of oven.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Wipe fish dry; salt and pepper to taste.
Dip in melted margarine, both sides.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Spoon onto aluminum foil or wax paper.

title: spring vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli and cauliflower.
Add soup, 1/2 cup cheese
and sour cream.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350° uncovered.	Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese
and French
fried
onions.
Bake 5 to 10 more minutes uncovered.

title: golden rich bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine. Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread evenly.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs and cream until fluffy. Pour over first mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
The cake will look somewhat like a custard.
Do not bake until firm. Cake should be soft in the middle.
Yield:
20 bars.
Each bar contains 192 calories.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar to eggs, beating thoroughly, then add chocolate mixture.
Fold in flour sifted with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in a shallow pan and bake in a slow oven (325°) for 30 minutes or until done.
(May take longer).
Remove from pan and cool slightly.
Cut in squares.

title: angel food cake(will serve 12 to 16.)
directions: Bake angel food cake as directed; cool.
Slice 1-inch from top and make a well, not through bottom or sides.
Mix 1 package vanilla pudding with cold milk; let thicken.
Take peach pie filling and 1/2 vanilla pudding; mix well.
Fill well with this. Whip the cream and add other 1/2 vanilla pudding.
Replace top of cake.
Ice with cream and vanilla pudding; place in freezer.
Just before serving, remove from freezer about 20 minutes.
Can be kept in refrigerator.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Butter 8 or 9-inch pan.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Test:
When dropped in very cold water, a soft ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature.

title: chocolate jubilee cake
directions: Grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix next 4 ingredients with mixer at high speed for 3 minutes.
At low speed, beat in real mayo until smooth.
Add flour mixture.
Beat just until smooth.
Stir in pie filling and raisins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove.
Cool.
Eat.
Enjoy.

title: banana peanut salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, margarine and juice from pineapple. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cool completely and add 3 cups of Cool Whip.
In large glass bowl alternate layers of bananas, pineapple, marshmallows and peanuts.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed peanuts.
Chill before serving.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes, then mash and add milk and butter to your taste.
Brown hamburg; drain fat.
Add tomato soup to hamburg and cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Put this mixture in microwave dish.
Put corn on top, then put potatoes on top of corn.
Heat in microwave for 5 minutes before serving.

title: angel pie
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and pineapple.
Remove from heat and add jello, Cool Whip and 1 large can Pet milk.
Be sure milk is very cold before whipping.
Fold into cooled pineapple mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 stick butter. Add all remaining ingredients; place in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: cheese marinated onions
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over onion rings.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all of the above and bake in pie crusts for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: mustard greens (rapys)
directions: Cut off stems, keeping flowers and leaves.
Wash thoroughly 3 times.
Drain.
Fry garlic in oil.
Add greens, salt and red pepper.
Simmer until tender.
Add a little water, if dry.

title: homemade tuna helper
directions: Bring macaroni and salt to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook until tender.
Drain.
Add soup and tuna; mix well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to butter mixture alternating with sour cream.
Mix well. Add vanilla. Bake in a tube pan that has been floured and greased at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Remove carefully from oven and let cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan. No frosting needed.

title: aunt turalee's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add egg; beat until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add gradually to liquid.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together salad oil, dill weed, lemon pepper, garlic powder and Ranch dressing mix.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Refrigerate until dough is quite firm.
Roll about 1/4 of dough out at a time on a floured board.
Roll about 1/8-inch thick.
Do not overwork dough or it will stick to the board.
Cut out cookies with cookie cutter and bake on cookie sheet in preheated 325° oven or until light brown. May be sprinkled with colored or plain sugar before baking.
For holiday cookies cut out with Christmas or gingerbread cutters. Makes about 80 (2-inch) round cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use orange juice for second cup of water for jello.
Combine ingredients and refrigerate.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for the margarine.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.
This doubles well and is always an "asked for" recipe.

title: turtle truffle tart
directions: Cream sugar and butter, gradually add flour, then remaining ingredients.
Press into bottom and up sides of 11-inch tart pan. Prick bottom with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden; cool.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Blend together oleo, powdered sugar and milk; then add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Roll into small balls.
Dip balls in mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin.
Keep paraffin mixture hot while dipping, using a double boiler.
Let stand until dry.
Before I add coconut and pecans to second mixture, I take out 1/2 of the mixture and chop maraschino cherries in it.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir 1 package soup
mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and chopped green onions.
Add shrimp or crab meat. Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: sweet seed dressing
directions: Combine honey, paprika, dry mustard, salt and lemon juice. Add oil in slow steady stream, beating constantly with electric mixer until thick.
Beat in seed.
Chill.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until it holds a point.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually.
When glossy, pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: chicken log
directions: Beat together first three ingredients.
Blend in next two ingredients and 2 tablespoons parsley; refrigerate remaining parsley.
Shape mixture into a 9-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: french silk pie
directions: Blend sugar and butter. Add vanilla and melted chocolate. Add first egg; beat for 5 minutes. Add second egg; beat for 5 minutes. Pour into cool, baked pie shell. Place in freezer for 1 hour.

title: nut cracker sheets
directions: Turn oven on to 350°.
Line a baking sheet with foil.
In a glass bowl, melt the butter in the microwave (45 seconds). Remove from heat.
Stir in the brown sugar.
Spoon the sugar mix on the crackers. Spread with a knife.
Sprinkle on the nuts. Put the pan in the oven and bake for about 7 to 9 minutes, until topping is bubbly.
When the crackers are cool, you can break into smaller pieces.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix together the milk and lemon juice; add drained pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Spoon into crusts.
Put in refrigerator.
Freezes good, too.
Makes 2 pies.

title: stickies
directions: After removing stickies from the oven, remove from muffin pan and spoon the icing over the stickies.
Chow down!!!

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs in bowl.
Add bananas, mixing well.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients gradually.
Pour into large, greased and floured loaf pan (you may also use two small loaf pans).
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: michelle's favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and ketchup in a bowl. Press into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; drain fat.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix with fingers.
Line loaf pan with oiled brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool completely or it will fall apart.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Squeeze cheese in a bowl.
Pour macaroni on it.
Put sugar in it.
You just stir it.
Put it in the oven.
Put it on the table. Put it in the microwave.
Put it out for people.

title: south county johnny cake
directions: Mix corn meal, salt, sugar, boiling water and a lump of butter, thinning down with rich milk, all the while stirring over low heat, 10 to 15 minutes to cook through.
Cream or milk is added from time to time until mixture is like mashed potatoes. Drop by tablespoon on hot greased griddle.
Cook until brown and turn over and brown the other side.
Serve piping hot with butter.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into serving portions.
Season with salt and pepper; roll lightly in flour.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken lightly on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Seed and place green pepper lengthwise.
Mix with chopped onion, chopped garlic and tomatoes.
Add this to chicken.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Add sliced mushrooms; simmer for about 15 minutes more.
Remove chicken to large platter; pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 generous portions.

title: low calorie tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and Sweet 'N Low;
beat	well.
Thoroughly stir in flour.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Roll dough	into
3/4-inch balls;
press flat with base of floured glass.
Bake
at 400° for 6
to 8	minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cakes;
35 calories per cookie.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, brown and white sugar.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: candied pecans
directions: Bring to
soft boil stage (236°) the first three ingredients. Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour out on wax paper.

title: tuna patties
directions: Crumble bread in the tuna and mix.
Add onion and egg.
Make into 6 to 8 patties and fry in a small amount of oil or grease.

title: lima beans and corned beef
directions: Cook dry limas until nearly done.
Add the finely chopped onion, then add the can of corned beef and season with salt and pepper.
Cook together for 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Yields approximately 4.

title: butterscotch pineapple bars
directions: Combine sugar, butter and orange peel.
Cream well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add pineapple, butterscotch chips and pecans; mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: southern salad
directions: Cut peppers in 1/2-inch strips.
Chop broccoli in bite size pieces.
Chop onion, cauliflower and tomatoes in 1/2-inch size pieces.
Crumble Feta cheese.
Cut lettuce in small strips.

title: apricot delight(my mother's recipe:  mrs. stella mccurdy)
directions: Combine pineapple, jello, baby food and 1/2 cup sugar into large pan.
Heat on simmer until thoroughly mixed.
Add cream cheese until blended into mixture.
Cool mixture in freezer (not to be warm).
When cool, fold in Cool Whip gently, until thoroughly blended.
Pour into cake pan or several small serving dishes.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook beef and sausage until well done, making a fine texture with fork while cooking.
Drain off fat.
Cook bacon crisp and crush over meats.
Open beans and drain off juice.
Mix beans, meats and all other ingredients together.
Bake in ovenproof bowl at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: zesty zucchini soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Add bouillon cubes stirring until dissolved.
Add vegetables; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Pour into blender; blend until smooth.
Return mixture to Dutch oven; stir in cream cheese, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot or chilled.
Makes 8 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: parmesan rolls
directions: Cut crusts off bread slices.
Divide slices into thirds. Layer stacks of bread as follows: 1 plain piece of bread, 1 piece dipped in batter and 1 plain piece of bread.
Cut 3 layer stack into fourths.
Dip quarters into melted butter and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Wrap all pieces in foil and refrigerate overnight to rise a bit.
When ready to serve, bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes and serve hot.

title: ole west chicken
directions: Brown chicken or pork chops in oil in heavy pan or skillet. Remove and add onions.
Remove and stir in chili powder.
Add pepper slices, rice, tomato sauce, water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Place chicken or pork and onion slices on top of rice mixture.
Cover and cook at 375° for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.

title: chocolate layered cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake crust according to mix; reserve some to garnish.
Press into 8-inch pie plate; chill.
Combine milk, cheese and cheesecake mix.
Beat at a low speed until blended. Beat on medium for 3 minutes until thick.
Place 1/3 in a small bowl.
Fold in cocoa.
Spread 1/2 vanilla over crust, then chocolate, then remaining vanilla.
Chill 1 hour.

title: bean and sausage
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces. Heat all ingredients as directed on package. Place in microwave. Place all precooked ingredients together in serving dish and season well to taste.

title: mini calzones
directions: Mix cheeses until well blended.
Place 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture on unfolded biscuit.
Place one slice of kielbasa on top of cheese and fold the biscuit over.
Secure the edges by pressing together.
Bake filled biscuits on a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add 6 to 8 slices of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hearty beef vegetable soup
directions: In large stock pot, combine beef bones, water and any stems and/or leaves from vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove meat from bones.
Strain broth and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Skim fat from broth.
Return to heat.
Add bouillon cubes, rice and seasonings.
Simmer until rice is tender.
Add vegetables and continue simmering until done. Makes approximately 4 quarts.
Freezes well.
A great project for a "cabin fever afternoon."

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk and sour cream.
Layer crust with bananas; spread pudding mix over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle pecans on Cool Whip; dot with cherries.

title: carrot salad(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Scrap and grate carrots.
Remove from bowl and chop again with knife.
Mix with mayonnaise and refrigerate.
At serving time, stir in chopped dates.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour and add to mixture.
Stir in coconut.
Bake in tube pan for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and green pepper over medium heat until beef is cooked.
Drain off fat.
Add to beef corn (with liquid), and both soups.
Combine with cooked noodles.
Place mixture in casserole and top with a sprinkling of cheese and onions, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine and toss lightly.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar and mustard to make mixture.

title: cheesy egg casserole
directions: Combine flour, salt and butter in large bowl.
Add eggs, cottage cheese, chilies and Jack cheese.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Garnish with pimientos and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Note:
Potatoes may be cooked and mashed several days ahead and kept in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: apple butterscotch bread
directions: Stir together mix, oats, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in butterscotch chips.
Stir in raisins.
Combine egg and milk. Stir into oat mixture.
Add applesauce and orange juice.
Beat mixture vigorously for 30 seconds.
Spoon into large greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
This recipe has very little fat in it!

title: pineapple cheese log
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Roll in coconut.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all, adding bananas just before serving, and serve chilled.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, melt 1 tablespoon margarine. Cook chicken 10 minutes, browned on both sides; remove. In remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook onion and mushrooms with garlic until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Return chicken into skillet; cover. Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring often. Serves 4. Good with baked potato, green onion and thyme.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake until firm.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: mixed nut chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes about 4 dozen pieces or 2 pounds.

title: wild rice and turkey salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cool.
Add turkey, mayonnaise, French dressing, salt, almonds and celery.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Just before serving, add oranges and pineapple.
Serve on lettuce.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Then the berries.
Lastly add the flour, salt and baking powder, sifted together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 cups hot water.
Drain the pineapple and save juice.
Add juice and ice to measure 2 cups.
Mix this into jello mixture.
When partially set, add pineapple and cut up banana.
When set, put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts. Easy and real good flavor!

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Cut loaves in half.
Gently stretch each half, then roll it out into a 10 x 14-inch rectangle.
Alternate layers of meat and cheese in the center of the dough.
Fold each side over once, pinching seams and tucking in the ends.
Sprinkle small amount of cornmeal on cookie sheet.
Lay stromboli on cornmeal with the folded side down.

title: early american buttermilk pie
directions: Partially bake pie crust.
Cool the crust 15 minutes before filling.
In a large bowl, stir the sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg together.
Using a wire whisk or wooden spoon, blend in the eggs. Add the buttermilk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into the cooled pie crust.
Cover the rim of the pastry with aluminum foil strips to prevent overbrowning.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until a knife inserted into the center comes out barely clean, about 45 to 55 minutes.
Transfer to a wire rack and cool to room temperature.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and eggs only until flour is well moistened.
Do not beat.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli jennifer
directions: Grease a 1
quart casserole with oleo.	Combine broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, cheese,
onion
and egg and blend.
Turn into baking dish;
sprinkle
with
cracker crumbs and dot with oleo. Bake until bubbly at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Mix in small pan Karo syrup, sugar and water.
Cook until it forms a thin thread, 6 to 8-inches long.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add syrup and beat until combined.
Add vanilla with syrup.
Mixture will be moist but stiff.

title: sadie moss' chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to which brandy flavoring has been added. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°, or until done. Cool and ice or serve plain.

title: bonny's chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Boil chicken.
Do not add salt.
Bone chicken and break in chunks.
In buttered casserole dish, layer as follows:
mushroom soup mixed with 1 can chicken broth, 1/2 stuffing mix, chicken, chicken soup mixed with 1 can chicken broth and remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add graham crackers.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients together until thick like a sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: coconut cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake cake according to instructions. While hot, pierce holes in top of cake.
Mix Eagle Brand and cream of coconut.
Pour mixture over cake and let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: sugarless applesauce
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook apples, soda and cinnamon until apples are tender, about 45 minutes.
Mash until consistency of applesauce.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Layer the following in a casserole dish:

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
together the corn, broccoli, egg, salt and pepper. Turn into
a
greased casserole dish and top with the cracker crumbs and
