melted
butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Make a 9-inch circle with refried beans on a foil covered cookie sheet.
Spread guacamole dip over refried beans.
Layer tomatoes, olives, eggs and cheese on top of guacamole and beans. Serve with Fritos, Doritos or any tortilla chips.

title: lo-cal ambrosia
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and chill.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Roast the pecans with the butter and let cool.
Whip the eggs for 10 minutes. Add the sugar, pudding, condensed milk and whole milk.
Beat and add to the pecans.
Pour in freezer and finish up with milk to make 1 gallon.

title: traditional smothered steak
directions: In skillet, or Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat. Saute onion until translucent; remove and set aside. In same skillet, saute round steak until browned. Meanwhile, stir together mushroom soup, onion soup mix, beef broth and 1 cup water until blended; add onion and pour over browned meat. Reduce heat, cover with tight fitting lid, and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until beef is fork tender, or for Dutch oven, cover and cook in preheated 350 degree oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vatapa(south american blend of broth, shellfish and nuts)
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp. Cover and bring to boil, stir often.
Add shrimp.
Simmer 5 minutes or until tender. Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla well.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Gradually add cake flour, sifted with baking powder.
Pour into waxed paper lined loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand in pan for 5 minutes before removing cake to cool.

title: tomato-mushroom sauce
directions: Saute
garlic
in
oil
in frying pan until golden. Add mushrooms and saute 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer,
uncovered,
hour
until
flavors are blended. This marinade
can
be
drained after using and stored, covered, in refrigerator to reuse.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: Combine sugar and orange peel.
Separate biscuits.
Dip each in melted butter and then coat with sugar mixture.
Overlap in ring mold (put them on a plate).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Invert over plate immediately.
Combine cheese and confectioners sugar; add orange juice.
Beat until smooth. Drizzle cream cheese mix over hot biscuits.

title: cabbage and carrots
directions: Heat oil in heavy pan over medium heat.
Add cabbage, carrots, onion and sugar.
Cook, stirring, until very well browned and softened (vegetables should scorch a little).
Remove from heat. Stir in soy sauce and vinegar.
Serve hot.

title: buttermilk meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients into little meat balls; fry in butter.

title: shimmering pineapple gelatin
directions: Drain juice from pineapple can; don't even take slices out of can.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Fill can of pineapple with gelatin.
Chill until set.

title: potato egg salad
directions: Boil potatoes for about 25 minutes so they are still firm; peel and cube.
Better if cooked the night before.
Chop up the eggs. Put all the ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
One-fourth cup half and half can be added to salad dressing if needed.

title: corn flake drops
directions: Beat egg whites until
stiff.
Add
sugar
slowly, then fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop batter from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in slow
oven	for
about 7 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add Ro-tel and taco seasoning.
In large oven-proof bowl, put meat mixture.
Add soup.
Break tortillas into bite sized pieces and stir into mix.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: kelly's favorite dinner
directions: In a saucepan, heat milk, butter and flour until mixture thickens (boils).
Meanwhile, saute green pepper and mushrooms until tender.
When milk mixture thickens, add chicken or turkey, green pepper, mushrooms, pimento, mushroom soup and peas.
Serve over rice, toast or pastry cup.

title: carlene's chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour in chicken broth 1 cup at a time, mixing together as you pour. Sprinkle in black pepper.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Make sure your dressing is real moist.
Pour into a baking pan.
Bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Save 1 cup broth to use while cooking Rice-A-Roni.
Cook as box directs, but substitute water for 1 cup broth.
Cook chopped broccoli.
In large casserole, layer Rice-A-Roni, broccoli, then chicken.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Mix mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth dessert
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: seafood sauce delight
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Open cans and drain juices into a large mixing cup.
Add enough water to juices to make 3 cups.
Mix with pudding and cook until thickened.
Let cool.
Place oranges, pineapples and peaches in large bowl.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit.
Chill.
Add sliced bananas before serving.

title: raspberry-nut pinwheels
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder onto waxed paper. Beat together
butter, sugar and egg in large bowl with electric
mixer until
fluffy.
Stir
in
vanilla.
Gradually add flour
mixture, stirring until well combined.
Roll out dough between 2 pieces of	waxed
paper
to 12 x 10-inch rectangle. Remove top
piece
of waxed
paper.
Spread
jam
evenly over entire surface
of dough.
Sprinkle evenly with nuts.	Firmly roll up	dough
from
a long side, jelly-roll style, removing waxed paper as you roll. Wrap roll in waxed paper and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve, place 2 well rounded teaspoonfuls in 1 cup boiling water.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
In a skillet, saute peppers in oil for 3 minutes.
Place hamburger and sauteed peppers in 3-quart casserole.
Add next 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine bread crumbs and sprinkle with butter.
Place on top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place broken bread in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Break eggs in a bowl and beat; add milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and butter.
Stir.
Pour over bread and mix well.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together until it snaps or to hard ball on candy thermometer.
Slowly stir this syrup into the well beaten whites to which has been added 6 marshmallows.
Beat constantly as long as you can without it becoming grainy.
Pour half into a well buttered square cake pan.
Spread with creamy peanut butter.
Add the remaining part after adding food coloring. Cut into squares.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar until resolved.
Cool slightly.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift, then measure flour.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add chopped nuts and coconut, if desired.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients in a large casserole dish. Mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1 stick margarine.
Toss the flakes in the margarine and sprinkle over the top of the casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken rellenos
directions: Pound each chicken breast to 1/4-inch thickness.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Combine chilies and pimentos.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon chile mixture over cheese.
Roll up chicken from short edge. Secure with toothpicks.

title: jalapeno bean dip
directions: Spread dip on the bottom of 2 pie plates.
Mix together sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning.
Spread tomato, onion, cheese and olives.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Place all ingredients in top of double boiler.
While cooking, beat with electric hand mixer until icing stands up in peaks. Remove from stove and frost cake.

title: zippy meat balls
directions: Beat egg in medium bowl.
Mix in bread crumbs, chili sauce, salt, onion, garlic powder, ground beef and celery.
Shape into 30 small balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Melt Crisco in large skillet over medium heat. Add meat balls and brown on all sides. Continue cooking until done, about 12 minutes, including browning time.
Warm barbecue sauce while meat balls are cooking.
Serve on wooden picks.
Dip in warm sauce.

title: plantain dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously. Chill at least 2 hours. Shake just before serving. Yield: 1/2 cup.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients together until like a pastry. Grease 8-inch square pan.
Press pastry on bottom and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour into your crust.
Chill.
May be topped with chopped nuts.

title: quick pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain and rinse with cool water. Put in large (plastic) container. Cover with dressing. Let sit while you cut up your vegetables. Add your choice of fresh raw vegetables. Stir and cover. Let sit in the refrigerator for 30 minutes. Then serve.

title: herbed rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo.
Add sugar, salt, milk, 6 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Stir until mixture forms ball.
Turn out on a well floured surface and knead, adding more flour if needed.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double bulk.
Roll out.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo and brush top.
Sprinkle with dill.
Roll up jelly roll, cut in 1 inch pieces.
Put in muffin tins.
Let raise 15 minutes.
Brush rolls with beaten egg. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9x13 inch dish.

title: chicken-waldorf salad
directions: Using a fork, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and salt in a large bowl.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: tortellini with chicken and pesto
directions: Puree the first 5 ingredients in processor until almost smooth. Season with salt and pepper.
(Can be made 1 day ahead. Transfer to small bowl.
Press plastic wrap directly onto surface of pesto to seal, cover and chill.)

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

scoop out pulp. Salt the insides of

Mince the pulp; measure 1
