of the tomatoes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter in large roaster pan.
Pour in all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Set oven at 200°.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: spicy gazpacho
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, use a wire whisk to blend remaining ingredients.
Add liquid to vegetable mixture, stirring to combine.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve cold.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields:
about 8 cups of soup.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and dry jello in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake
at
for
1 hour. Immediately after removing from
oven
glaze
with: 1 cup powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons
lemon
juice
and 1 teaspoon white vanilla (optional).
Mix thoroughly and pour over cake so that all is covered.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately, beating well.
Place juice and rind and beat well.
Place in greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cucumber-pineapple salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and chill until thickened. Add the remaining ingredients and pour in mold. Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: downy light cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar; add shortening, milk, and egg whites and beat for 2 minutes. Add flavoring and mix; pour into two 8 inch cake pans that have been floured and greased. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. For filling, in between layers or on top, use pineapple, apple, or just about any fruit that you desire.

title: blueberry muffins(to rival jordan marsh's famous one)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Flour the berries with some of the flour mixture.
Add vanilla to sugar and egg.
Add the rest of the flour mixture, alternating with the milk and mix thoroughly.
Carefully, stir the berries into the flour mixture.
Sprinkle the tops of the muffins with the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(Store uncovered.
If covered tightly, they will become soggy overnight.)

title: kugelhopf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix well 2 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Heat milk, raisins, butter and water to 120° to 130°. Butter need not melt.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes or until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in lemon peel and 1 1/2 cups flour or enough to make a thick batter.
Cover in warm place.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled.

title: taco tray dip
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients and spread on tray.
Add a little salt sprinkled lightly.
Top with the remaining ingredients.
Spoon 1 jar taco sauce over this and top with more cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: fisherman spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and keep warm.
Melt butter and add garlic, saute.
Add mushrooms, green onions, shrimp and crabmeat. Saute just until shrimp turns pink and mixture is hot.
Toss with spaghetti.
Garnish with green onions.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy cornbread dressing
directions: Follow cooking directions on cornbread mix package.
Saute celery and onion in 1 stick of oleo.
Crumble cornbread.
Add celery and onion.
Add soups and broth.
Place in greased oblong dish.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven until firm.

title: broccoli christmas wreath
directions: Arrange fresh broccoli into a wreath on a plate or tray. Start with the bottom layer, then arrange the top layer.
This should be in a round wreath shape with the center empty.
Place the tomatoes on top of the broccoli to look like holly berries on a Christmas wreath.
Serve with vegetable dip.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar, add milk, lemon zest and lemon juice. Pour into baked shell.
Freeze.
When ready to serve decorate with whipped cream.

title: bean salad
directions: Cut lettuce up into small pieces.
Add mayonnaise, drained beans and diced onion.
Mix ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Form into small balls.
Melt together chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: 7-up cake and icing
directions: Beat all ingredients together except 7-Up.
Mix well; add 7-Up and beat again.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: best ever strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries and drain completely on paper towel.
Mash 1 1/2 boxes of berries.

In separate bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch. Arrange the other 1 1/2 boxes of berries in pie shell; set aside. Combine mashed berries and sugar mixture in medium saucepan; bring to boil on high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium-low and continue to stir until thickened.
Pour over berries in shell and cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat powdered sugar, 2 sticks oleo and 2 eggs for 10 to 15 minutes; spread over crust.
Slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix bananas with crushed pineapple.
Spread over powdered sugar mixture layer.
Spread Cool Whip over banana mixture layer.
Top Cool Whip with 1 can cherry pie filling and pecans.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage quarters in boiling, salted water until just tender; drain and dice in large pieces.
Place half of cabbage in greased casserole.
Add half of the soup, cheese and onions. Repeat layers.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: herbed chicken fettuccine
directions: Combine Season-All and poultry seasoning; sprinkle over chicken.
Saute chicken in oil and 2 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes until juices run clear.
Add water, teriyaki sauce, onion soup mix and 2 tablespoons of herb soup mix.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain noodles, add to chicken.
Add cheese, Worcestershire, remaining butter and herb soup mix.
Toss to coat.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Combine strawberries, oil and eggs; add to flour mixture. Mix and add nuts. Bake in greased pans 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix sugar, spices, flour and tapioca together.
Stir in chopped tomatoes; stir to coat tomatoes.
Put into 8-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with vinegar and dot with butter.
Top with other crust and bake as you would any fruit pie.

title: savory stuffed rib roast
directions: Crisp cook and crumble bacon. Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Set bacon aside. Cook onion and garlic in reserved drippings until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in olives and bacon.
Unroll roast; spread bacon mixture over meat.
Re-roll roast.
Tie securely.
Place meat, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper. Insert a meat thermometer.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours for rare or until thermometer reads 140°.
Let roast stand, covered with foil, about 15 minutes before removing strings and carving.

title: pumpernickel with dip
directions: Mix all together.
Scoop out bread.
Fill and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add lemon juice.
Add finely grated or chopped onion and bell pepper to cheese mixture.
Add Worcestershire sauce and red pepper to taste.
Roll mixture into one large ball or two small balls.
You may roll to coat with parsley, chopped pecans and/or paprika.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: blue ribbon bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and garlic in large pot. Cover with 1/3 cup salt and ice for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine sugar, turmeric, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over drained cucumbers and heat just to boiling.
Seal in jars that have been sterilized.
Use a boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: herbed pretzels
directions: Mix together.
Pour over pretzels and toss.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 250°.
(Stir after 15 minutes of baking time.)

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in taco seasoning, until well mixed.
In a glass pie plate or serving dish, spread lettuce on bottom, then sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and tomatoes.
Serve with Tostitos or favorite corn chips.

title: lone ranger chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Arrange in buttered baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon over chicken; coating well.
Bake for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 400° oven.
Serves 4.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix well.
Bake on hot griddle, turning once.

title: oatmeal raspberry muffins
directions: *To make buttermilk, pour 1 tablespoon vinegar into measuring cup. Fill remainder with regular milk.

title: fruit bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut margarine into dry ingredients, press 1/2 mixture in an 8-inch pan (nonstick).
Spread fruit over crumbs in pan.
Cover fruit with other 1/2
of crumbs.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix.
Bring the following to a boil:
3/4 cup vinegar, 1/4 cup salad oil and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over the mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onion, water chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise. Top with Ritz crackers and drizzle butter or margarine on top of greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple taffy salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, egg, vinegar and drained pineapple juice from the crushed pineapple.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick (doesn't take long).
Cool in refrigerator. When cool, add fruits, nuts and Cool Whip.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fresh tomato and basil with angel hair pasta
directions: Cook pasta to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with hot water.
Keep warm.
In large skillet, heat oil; lightly saute zucchini and garlic.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and pepper.
Cook until thoroughly heated and slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese zucchini teasies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except bread to make a spread.
Spread on bread slices.
Place on baking sheet lined with foil.
Bake 12 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: caramel coffee cake
directions: Grease sides and bottom of Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Cut frozen rolls in half and stack them in the pan. Sprinkle dry pudding on top of rolls.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and pour over top of rolls.
Cover and let sit out overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let sit out 10 minutes or so before turning upside-down on plate.
Remove pan.
Best when served warm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar, flour, eggs and cinnamon.
Lightly stir in carrots and nuts.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or less.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together the butter, salt and sugar well.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Place on wire rack to cool completely before serving.
Has a rich, buttery flavor.

title: fruit dip
directions: Heat marshmallow cream in microwave for 30 seconds until creamy, then in large bowl, mix Cool Whip and marshmallow cream. Add cherry juice to color.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Heat slowly and boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: hot chicken salad(for brunch)
directions: Break 2 slices of bread into cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cooked, cut chicken, chopped vegetables, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Spoon over cubed bread.
Trim crust off 6 slices of bread.
Lay on top of mixture.
Combine eggs and milk. Pour over all.
Spoon soup over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Sprinkle cheese over top last 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Also good with turkey or corn.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift into a large bowl, flour and sugar.
Mix in saucepan and bring to a boil, butter or margarine, cooking oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix and pour into a large cookie sheet, slightly greased.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade chicken 'n' dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until cooked thoroughly.
When done, debone chicken and place back in broth (if broth level is low add 1 to 2 cups of water).
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine flour and Crisco, mix and cut until in small lumps.
Add milk and mix well.
Bring broth to boil.
Meanwhile, roll out dough on a bed of flour until thin.
Cut into small squares and place squares into boiling broth.
Stir and cook for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: While potatoes are warm, pour dressing over and chill for 2 hours.
Add celery and onion.
Chop egg whites; add.
Sieve yolks; reserve some for garnish.
Combine remaining sieved yolk with mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish mustard.
Fold into salad. Add salt and celery seed to taste.
Chill salad.
Add diced cucumber to trim; sprinkle reserved sieved yolk and sliced onion tops over top of salad.
Serves 8.

title: tuna sandwiches
directions: Beat together cream cheese and mustard until smooth; stir in tuna, celery and peanuts.
Spread on bread.
Top with tomato and lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: almond-crusted turkey patties
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix turkey, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onions and eggs.
Shape into four patties, each 3/4 inches thick. Coat both sides of patties with almonds.
Place patties on rack in broiler pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until patties are no longer pink inside.
Yields 4 servings, 365 calories per serving.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions on box.
Spoon mixture around inside of 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Place broccoli spears in center of "well."
Melt margarine in saucepan and add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in bouillon.
Gradually add milk, cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Add cream cheese and salt; stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in onions.

title: chicken cacciatore(this is a popular recipe in my house.)
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
In a large skillet, heat oil and fry chicken, turning occasionally, until lightly brown.
Add chopped peppers, and cook 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and spaghetti sauce. Cover.
Cook on simmer 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is done. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Serves 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 5 minutes; you can put the cinnamon stick in mixture.
After mixture has boiled 5 minutes, add the beets.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add butter; salt and pepper to taste.

title: breakfast shake
directions: Blend yogurt, berries and vanilla in blender, just enough to mix.
Add ice cubes to the blender, 1 or 2 at a time, through the hole in top of blender lid.
Whip until desired thickness.
Makes 2 servings.

title: raisin sauce (for ham)(diet)
directions: Mix Sweet 'N Low brown, mustard and flour.
Add raisins, vinegar and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine wafers, sugar, cocoa and syrup and mix well.
Add nuts and liquor.
Shape into bite-size balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins until puffy; drain and cool.
Mix flour, raisins and nuts to prevent sinking to the bottom of pan.
Mix as any other cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Bake in tube pan.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan; drain.
Add hash browns, peppers, onion, celery and eggs.
Mix butter in a large (13 x 9 x 2-inch or larger) casserole or spray with nonstick spray.
Place taco mixture in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and heat until melted.
To serve, place a large scoop of potato mixture on a warmed tortilla; add picante sauce, if desired; roll up and enjoy.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine with soups, broth and chilies. Add chicken and heat well.
In large baking dish, place a layer of tortillas, chicken sauce and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat until used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add slightly thawed strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Place half of the mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over top. Carefully spoon remaining strawberry mixture over. Chill until firm.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, in 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat unpeeled potatoes and enough water to cover to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until potatoes are fork-tender. Drain. Cool potatoes slightly. Peel and dice potatoes.

title: kielbasa snacks
directions: Boil kielbasa and cool slightly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Combine chili sauce, brown sugar and whiskey in a crock-pot; add sliced kielbasa.
Cook on high for 3 hours.

title: crunchy pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Sift flour and add alternating with milk. Add vanilla. Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix together well the first 6 ingredients.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over bean mixture.

title: mexican quiche without crust
directions: Mix ingredients and transfer to a 9 x 13-inch pan (casserole/quiche pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: bacon wrapped pretzels
directions: Wrap bacon around pretzel in a swirl pattern.
Place 6 to 8 wrapped pretzels on a microwave-safe plate or bacon rack. Microwave approximately 3 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Drain on paper towel.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough into jellyroll pan and bake according to package directions.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice; spread over baked cookie dough.
Cut into squares (a pizza cutter works great).
Place sliced fruit onto each square. Keep refrigerated.

title: "cheat" chili
directions: Wonderful on a cold day!
I buy the different dried beans in the fall and mix in large container for future use.
Sharing the recipe and a bag of mixed beans, with my friends, has become a "First Cold Day" tradition.
I truly do miss the snow!

title: golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Spread 1/3 pudding mixture over bottom layer of cake.
Top with second layer. Repeat layering, ending with pudding.
Chill 30 minutes. Sprinkle with sliced almonds and garnish with pineapple slices. Serves 12.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 12 hours.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crumble cookies (save 1 cup for topping).
Melt margarine; add to cookies and put in 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat broth in saucepan (2-quart).
Add potatoes, pepper and seasoning salt.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Do not drain. Layer potato mixture and Swiss cheese in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven until top is golden and potatoes are tender.

title: felicia dodges' new england baked beans
directions: Soak beans, onion and cut up salt pork overnight.
In the morning, parboil for about 1 hour.
Do not change liquid.
Put in covered 2-quart casserole dish and add all other ingredients.
Add water to cover beans totally.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 60 minutes. Turn down to 220° and bake 6 to 7 hours, adding water if necessary.
Beans should not be dry.
Liquid is very tasty.

title: lemon dainty
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add egg yolks, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat well until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole dish; set in pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: *Omit salt if using Puff Corn.

title: apple niki muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk and margarine in separate bowl.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Blend only until flour is moist.
Fold in apples.

title: wings in oyster sauce
directions: Scald wings in boiling water.
Pat dry.
Brown in 1/2 c. cooking oil using large skillet.
Drain oil.
Add 1 c. water & all spices.
Simmer with lid on until done (about 10 minutes).

title: freezer cucumber pickles(easy...no canning involved)
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, salt and celery seed in a large bowl.
Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan; cook mixture over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cucumbers. Cover and refrigerate 48 hours.
Spoon cucumber mixture into 1/2 pint jars or freezer containers; seal, label and freeze for up to 6 months.
Thaw before serving.
Yields 8 half pints or 4 pints.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Use an angel cake pan.
Cream the shortening and sugar, then add one egg at a time.
Blend after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet until meat is done and onion is tender.
Spoon off excess fat.
Stir in next four ingredients.
Cover and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and Parmesan.
Return to heat.
Stir until cream cheese is melted and well combined.
Serve warm with crackers, chips, etc.

title: roasted red peppers and garlic spread
directions: Blend all ingredients.	Serve cold or at room temperature with bread.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: earthquake cake(or deluxe german chocolate cake)
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box.
Set aside.
Layer coconut on bottom of greased pan.
Cover coconut with pecans and pour cake mixture over this.
In large bowl, mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cake batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until cake springs back or until done.

title: mexican black beans with rice
directions: Bring water to boil in medium saucepan.
Add the rice and boil until level of water just covers the rice.
Stir often.
Cover. Reduce heat to low and cook 20 minutes.
Drain black beans; rinse and drain again.
Break up the tomatoes with a fork, if too large.

title: coconut brownies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Don't overbake.)

title: cheese puff bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 2-quart saucepan, bring the water to a boil.
Add the Bisquick and stir vigorously over medium heat until the mixture leaves the side of the pan, forming a ball. Cool 5 minutes.
Beat one egg at
a time into the mixture, beating thoroughly.
Add garlic salt and cheese.
Drop by a spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 15 minutes.
(Should be golden brown.)
Serve hot.
Makes four servings.

title: frozen fruit fluff
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover and freeze for 8 hours or overnight. May be frozen for up to 1 month. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: no-cook icing
directions: Put salt in egg whites along with 2 or 3 drops of cold water. Beat until peaks form.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add syrup and vanilla and beat until thick and smooth.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Place caramels in top of double boiler until just melted.
Add milk and nuts.
Mix and spoon onto greased wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Freeze about 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Drop cookies 1 teaspoon apart.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and margarine together in microwave until syrupy.
Pour over Chex and stir until well coated.
Add sugar and stir until well coated.

title: chicago style deep dish pizza
directions: Dissolve the yeast in water in a large bowl. Add the oils, cornmeal and 3 cups of the flour. Beat for 10 minutes with a mixer.
Put the dough hook on the mixer and mix in the additional 2 1/2 cups flour.
Knead for several minutes with the mixer.
Pour dough out and cover with a very large metal bowl. Allow to rise until doubled.
Punch down and allow to rise again.
Punch down. Oil two 9 or 10-inch round cake pans.
Put half of the dough in each and push out to edges using your fingers.
Crust should run up the side of pan and be about 1/8-inch thick.
Preheat oven to 475°.

title: fudge
directions: Add all ingredients.
Boil until hard ball.
Then add peanut butter.
Then let harden.

title: cheesy blue gills
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a bag and shake well.
In another dish, beat the eggs, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Set aside.
Crush the crackers.
Shake fillets in seasoned flour to coat, then dip in egg mixture.
Roll in cracker crumbs and fry in vegetable oil for 3 to 5 minutes or lightly brown.
Enjoy.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast (dissolved in warm water).
Work dough. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Remove amount needed.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Make a sauce of the Mazola, cornstarch, seasonings and milk. When boiling, add the cheese and stir until dissolved.
Oil a baking dish with Mazola; put in the potatoes and cheese sauce, mixed.
Cover with bread crumbs, moistened with Mazola.
Bake from 35 to 40 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute livers and sausage until browned.
Remove from skillet; drain and set aside.
Saute onions, celery, parsley and garlic in butter until tender.
Add livers, sausage and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until heated throughout, stirring constantly.
Serves 8.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If apples are juicy, may bake longer.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add 10x sugar and milk; mix well.
Fold Cool Whip in mixture.
Pour into baked pie crusts.
Chill until firm.
Add crushed peanuts on top of pies, if desired.
Makes 2 pies.

title: french canadian meat pie(tourtiere)
directions: Mix pork, onion and seasonings, then add bay leaf and water. Simmer uncovered 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Cool meat and skim off fat.
Line 9-inch pie pan with uncooked pie crust and fill with meat mixture.
Cover with pastry, seal edges and cut small vents in top crust.
Bake at 425° (218°C) until lightly browned, about 1/2 hour.

title: green pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup, cheese, milk and butter.
Pour over layered vegetables, eggs and crackers.
Bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: crunchy cheese potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, milk, chives, salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Spread in 13 x 10-inch pan.
Combine cheese and cornflakes, sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° until tender.
Allow 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate sombrero cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Dust with confectioners sugar or frost with glaze.

title: goof proof cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl combine 1
1/2 cups of flour and yeast. Heat milk, sugar, butter
and
salt
until
butter
is
almost melted, stirring
constantly.
Add
milk
mixture	to
flour mixture; add eggs.
Beat with
electric
mixer
on low for 30 seconds. Beat on high for
minutes
(dough
will be soft). Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead in remaining flour. Shape dough into
a
ball.	Place dough in lightly greased bowl; turn once.	Cover
with
warm,
damp
towel; let rise in a warm place until double (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork; blend in sugar, salt, beaten egg and butter.
Add water and flour.
Blend.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: our favorite chicken pot pie
directions: Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over pie.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup cold water.
Soak gelatin in remaining cold water (1/4 cup).
Add hot water to starch mixture and cook over medium heat until it comes to a boil and is clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in softened gelatin.
Add soap or detergent.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool and divide into five portions.
Put into jars and mix in food coloring to desired intensity.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apple.
Add sugar and marshmallows.
Add nuts (optional).
Mix and let set overnight.

title: one cup pie
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour and gradually add milk.
Pour peaches into melted margarine and then pour flour mixture over peaches.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.
You can substitute any kind canned fruit.

title: super easy cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place paper baking cups in each of 12 regular-size muffin cups or grease and flour muffin cups. Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly. Beat on medium speed 4 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Fill muffin cups about 1/2 full. Bake 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Immediately remove from pan; cool. Frost, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop.
Using a large casserole dish, place all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs, cherry jello, water, Wesson oil and crushed pineapple.
Mix well and bake for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
When done, remove from oven; pour juice from the pineapple over the cake while hot.
Remove cake from pan before pouring on the juice.
Refrigerate overnight, then before serving, spread the Cool Whip over the cake; cover this with cherry pie filling.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Crush cookies fine.
Spread half of cookies in bottom of dish.
Cream butter. sugar, and egg yolks; beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread this mixture over cookie crumbs; spread blueberries over this and sprinkle nuts over blueberries.
Spread whipped cream over nuts.
Sprinkle rest of cookie crumbs over top.

title: my prize winning salad dressing
directions: Cook in double boiler or in a heavy saucepan, stirring until thick.
Flavor with salt, pepper and butter.
I always mix it with sour cream when I make cabbage.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil and cook bell pepper and onions until tender.
Add flour and seasoning, mix well.
Add tomatoes, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Add raw shrimp and cook 5-10 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.
8-10 servings.

title: 7-layered salad
directions: Put vegetables in colander.
Break up the lettuce on bottom of salad bowl.
Layer remaining vegetables in bowl.
Spread mayo or salad dressing to cover.
Sprinkle sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Top with slices of crumbled bacon and hard-boiled eggs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving and add diced tomatoes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Coca-Cola.
After mixing for 2 minutes, add Coca-Cola.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: In large bowl, mix cottage cheese and pineapple; stir in the jello and vanilla.
Add the Cool Whip last.
Mix well and refrigerate.
It can be served right away.

title: apple sauté
directions: In a large saucepan or skillet, melt butter.
Add apples, stirring constantly until apples are tender, about 6 to 7 minutes.

title: lois' maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into cakes and roll in the bread crumbs.
Place in refrigerator for about 1/2 hour.
Fry in deep fat or sauce in light oil, covered.

title: chicken casserole(serves 8)
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix broth with dressing.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Layer in oblong 9 x 12-inch pan in this order: dressing, chicken and mixed ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Thaw before baking.

title: crockpot italian beef
directions: Place beef roast in crockpot.
Add gravy mix, water and peppers - juice and all.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix with your hands. Makes 2 crusts.

title: cherry cream crown
directions: Line 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers (bottom and sides).
Soften cream cheese and cream it with sugar.
Whip cream and vanilla.
Fold with cream cheese.
Alternate layers of cream mix and ladyfingers.
Chill at least 2 hours, overnight is better. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 18 muffin pan cups.
Combine flour, sugar, spices, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix pumpkin, eggs and margarine until blended.
Stir in chips.
Pour over flour mixture and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into pan until 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until puffed and springy to the touch.
Remove and serve warm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in 12 x 13-inch pizza pan at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked stir-fry chicken
directions: Dip chicken breast pieces into eggs, then bread crumbs.
Brown in frypan, put aside.
Then stir-fry vegetables in oil.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Put stir-fry vegetables on top of the chicken, then put Cheddar cheese on top, then add chopped tomatoes to top. Put in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with white rice.

title: pork cake
directions: Grind raisins and citron together.
Pour boiling coffee over ground salt pork; add raisins and citron and stir well.
Add brown sugar and beaten eggs.
Stir baking soda into molasses and add to batter.
Sift flour with remaining dry ingredients and stir into batter (add more flour if needed).
Bake in two greased loaf pans at 325° or until done.

title: energy candy(great snack for children)
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter in
bowl.
Gradually add dry milk, mixing well.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Shape into log; wrap.
Chill until firm.

title: favorite baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Remove fat from pan and fry hamburger and onion until lightly browned.

Mix beans, spices and meats together in a large bowl, then pour in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour or 325° for a little longer. This can be made the day before, refrigerated and baked the next day.
Takes a little longer to bake when cold.

title: ribs and parsley rice
directions: Prepare ribs.
Place ribs, salt, pepper, vinegar and onion (sliced) in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and cook for 45 minutes. Remove ribs from water and place them in a baking pan and bake until desired tenderness (barbecue sauce is optional).
Take liquid from ribs and add the 2 cups rice.
Cook on low heat until rice is cooked.
Serve with vegetables and rolls for a complete and delicious meal.

title: katie's apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Place into a 9-inch square pan.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and sprinkle over apple filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with marshmallows; brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beans, ketchup, brown sugar, syrup, onion, salt and pepper together.
Put in pan.
Place bacon slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: hidden sloppy joe
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in ketchup, mustard and soup, heating until boiling; simmer 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°. Grease a Bundt pan.
Mix Bisquick, milk, margarine and eggs, beating for 30 seconds.
Spread 2 cups of batter on bottom and up sides of pan 2-inches, also up the center of pan.
Put beef mixture on top of this and spread remaining batter, by teaspoon, on top of beef.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together. Add egg and beat. Now, add lemon juice, blending well, then add water and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add butter. Beat egg whites until creamy and gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar and a pinch of cream of tartar. Beat until it forms soft peaks.

title: low-fat mexican spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat; saute onion and garlic in Butter Buds.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add broth and tomatoes (with tomato juice).
Add spaghetti pieces to tomato mixture.
Add picante sauce and cumin; simmer while covered until spaghetti is cooked. Add chicken and spoon into casserole dish, sprayed with non-fat cooking spray.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until very tender.
Cut into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of long baking dish.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles by package directions.
Lightly brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion and drain.
Blend in sauce, salt and oregano.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: In a skillet, brown onion in margarine. Grease a 11x13 pan and spread potatoes in bottom, cover with cooked onion. In a bowl mix together soups, sour cream and cheese. Spread over onions and potatoes. Mix cornflakes with softened butter and sprinkle over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350 for an hour.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Grease baking dish.
Put cut bread on bottom of pan.
Add sausage, then cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and soup.
Pour on top. Cover casserole and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours covered.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and put bacon on top in baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of 9 x 12 pan. Bake crust at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: harvard beets
directions: Make a sauce by cooking together for 5 minutes.
Pour over canned beets and let stand for a few minutes.
Add some butter.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Thaw fish; skin fish and cut into 1-inch square pieces.
In saucepan, fry onion in butter until cooked.
Add potatoes, water, salt, pepper and fish.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes or until potatoes are cooked.
Add milk and corn.
Heat again.
Serve with cornbread.
Enjoy!

title: deep dish tuna pie
directions: In large skillet, cook onion and potato in water, covered, 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in soup, milk, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, dill weed and pepper.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and tuna.
Spoon into an ungreased 2-quart casserole; roll out pastry and put over top of casserole.
Brush crust with beaten egg.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fantastic pudding
directions: Mash strawberries and mix with sugar.
Refrigerate overnight. Mix pudding and milk according to directions.
Layer in a large bowl the wafers, bananas, strawberries and pudding until you reach top of bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 5
persons.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add beans and onion.
Toss well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: jello bavarian pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and frozen strawberries.
Stir gently until fruit thaws.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add whipped topping and blend until smooth. Mixture may appear slightly curdled, but will smooth out on blending.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.

title: easy strawberry jelly
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly.
Set aside.
Stir Sure-Jell with water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir mixture together until sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour into plastic containers; cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours. Jelly is not ready to use.
Store in refrigerator or freezer. Makes 4 (1 cup) containers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and salt well.
Add cream cheese a little at a time.
Mix until extremely smooth.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla quickly to keep light and creamy.
(Add raisins to personal taste.)
Pour into pie pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until set.

title: apple dip
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate. Delicious with all kinds of fresh fruit!

title: turtles
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar, margarine and salt together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup water; cool.
Also cook prunes in 1 cup water and cool.
Dredge walnuts and raisins in flour.
Beat eggs and applesauce.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes a 350° until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Cool on wire racks.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Add flour to other ingredients and mix well.
Roll cookies into balls and crisscross with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in 1/2-inch balls, then roll each ball in 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mrs. field's cookies(serves 112)
directions: Measure oatmeal.
Put small amounts into blender and blend until it turns to powder.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, blended oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all together and add a 24 ounce bag chocolate chips, 1 (8 ounce) bag (Hershey) grated and/or 3 cups chopped nuts.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake golf ball size cookies.
Place 2 inches apart and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Allowing 1/2 onion per serving, cut large Bermuda or Spanish onions in 1/3 to 1/4-inch thick slices.
Separate into rings.
Dry thoroughly; coat generously with flour.
Using tongs, dip rings into thin fritter batter (follows), letting excess drip off.
Fry a few at a time in 1/2 to 1-inch deep hot fat or oil for about 2 minutes or until golden.
Drain.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Add margarine to sifted ingredients until mixture looks coarse.
Stir in currants and caraway seed.
Add buttermilk gradually; mix well. Knead dough until not sticky.
Cut dough in half; shape into ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cut a cross on top.
Bake until golden.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt into first mixture.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Crushed pineapple may also be added.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham.
Roll ham with asparagus and stick with toothpick.

title: chicken, black bean and barley soup
directions: Cover beans in pot with water.
Bring to a boil; cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Return pot to low heat.
Add chicken, onion and celery.
Add water to cover; cook 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Add barley, salt, pepper, mustard and cayenne.
Cook 30 minutes, until beans and barley are tender.
Remove chicken from bones and shred.
Return meat to the soup.
Serve with warm, buttered cornbread squares.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine in an ovenproof casserole dish.
Cook for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cover for 30 minutes of cooking.
Take cover off for the last 15 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except crab meat) tender.
Then add crab meat close to serving time.
Add cayenne pepper if you want it spicier.
Close copy to soup served at Wharf at Annapolis.

title: sun city appetizers
directions: Crumble and brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain fat.
Add cheese, oregano, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Spread on party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and put in freezer.
Once frozen, place in freezer bags.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes to serve.

title: peaches n' cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into 9-inch square baking pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place peaches over batter.
In separate bowl, cream together cheese, peach juice and sugar.
Spoon mixture over peaches.
Spread to cover peaches completely.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool at least 45 minutes before serving.
Yields 12 servings; each serving contains 304 calories (41% from fat).

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a 3-quart heavy saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. If sugar crystals form on sides of pot, wipe off with damp cloth. Continue cooking to the hard ball stage (252°).

title: candied peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and bring to a boil; add peanuts.
Cook until all water is gone, stirring from time to time, about 15 minutes.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: fresh corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set and lightly browned on top. Do not overcook or it will separate.

title: pot roast with vegetables
directions: Heat cooking oil in Dutch oven or heavy kettle with a cover. Add meat and brown well on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add water.
Cover and simmer gently for 2 hours, turning roast several times for even cooking.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine until onions are glossy.
Add water, wine and bouillon.
Simmer until cooked down.
Place in soup crocks.
Top with thick slice of French bread.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and Swiss cheese. Place under broiler until cheese is melted and browned.

title: chamorro shrimp patties
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Heat oil to 350°.
Drop from spoon into hot fat.
Fry until golden.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk and sugar in bowl with wire until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and lemon peel.
Stir in Cool Whip. Spread evenly in crust.
Press strawberries in covering the mixture.
Reserve some for garnish.
Pour milk in bowl; add pudding and beat with whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 1 minute.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon over strawberries in crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Garnish with strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix ingredients and heat in skillet.
Serve on buns.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix half of whipped cream with mayonnaise.
Cut pineapple and peach halves
into	pieces	(bite
size).
Drain fruit well.
In large serving
bowl layer fruit and mayonnaise-cream mixture. First pineapple,
then
bananas,
then peaches, then grapes and then cream	mixture.
Repeat
until
all
fruit and cream mix is used.
Sprinkle
each
layer with a little sugar. Spread remaining whipped cream
on
top and sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: snickerdoodles(yield: 54 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar and 3/4 cup granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook beans in one gallon of water until tender.
Salt to taste.
Brown onion, garlic, and sliced sausage in skillet until lightly browned; add to beans.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, and hot sauce.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Separate egg yolks.
Beat in top of double boiler.
Add sugar, cocoa, flour and a little milk to mix well, then add remaining milk.
Cook until thick in a double boiler.
Add vanilla.
Place vanilla wafers in bottom of dish.
Add pudding and wafers alternately.
Top with meringue.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, egg and rice.
Set aside.
Pour tomato juice in large boiler; add sugar and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil. Roll ground beef into balls.
Add to tomato juice.
Cook for about 35 minutes or until meat is well done.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream, in an electric mixer until well mixed, then fold in sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with round buttery crackers.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Cook on low heat until thick.
Pour in cooked pie shell. Makes 2 pies.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Into a small bowl, put both packages yeast.
Pour over this 1 cup of warm water.
Let stand while other ingredients are mixed. Melt Crisco.
Add other cup of warm water, sugar, salt and beaten eggs.
Stir well.
Have sifted flour in a large bowl.
Mix biscuits.
Place in a covered bowl in refrigerator at least 6 hours before using.

title: kielbasa hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1/4-inch rounds.
Mix brown sugar and ketchup together in saucepan over medium heat.
Add kielbasa rounds into sauce and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve in chafing dish for a party.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix well coarsely crushed pretzels and melted butter.
Mix well, press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Soften 8 ounce package cream cheese.
Mix in 1 cup sugar.
Whip 1 package Dream Whip according to package.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Dissolve 6 ounce package of strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 20 ounce package of frozen strawberries.
Stir until strawberries are melted.
When almost set, spread over cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Melt cream cheese in tomato soup; cool.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water and add to tomato soup mixture.
Stir in mayo, chopped vegetables and shrimp.
Pour into greased mold and refrigerate until set.
Serve with your favorite crackers.
This is a great holiday hors d'oeuvre.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots, then drain.
Saute sliced onion in butter.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard, then milk.
Cook, stirring until smooth. Add pepper and celery salt.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer carrots and cheese, then repeat.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pinto bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into the 3 pie shells. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell and bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Top with streusel and bake 15 more minutes.

title: meat and vegetable pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet and drain well.
Add seasonings and soup.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: u.s. senate restaurant bean soup
directions: Take pea beans and wash thoroughly, then run hot water through until beans are white again.
Mine never look really white, just shriveled.
Put on fire with hot water, then take ham hock.
Rinse and put in pot with beans.
Boil approximately 3 hours in covered pot.
When done or almost done, saute onion diced in a little butter until lightly brown.
Put in soup and continue to cook about 1/2 hour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Do not salt until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat 2 heaping tablespoons of flour with the first egg.
Add other two eggs and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Heat oven to 450°.
Place pie into oven and turn temperature down to 350°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: strawberry pizza pie
directions: Melt margarine with flour.
Press into pan and add nuts on top.
Press in.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool completely.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Spray glass baking dish with Pam.
Spread rice evenly in bottom of pan.
Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Add 1 1/2 cups hot water, salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil. Pour soup over chicken and rice.
Return to oven 15 to 20 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and chicken tests done with a fork.

title: super moist orange cake
directions: Cream cake mix with oil; add eggs and orange slices with juice.
Beat until creamy.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender.
Remove skin and bones. Break into bite-size pieces.
Mix together the soup, the cottage cheese, chiles, onions, tomatoes and chicken pieces.
In a 3-quart buttered casserole dish, place a layer of tortilla pieces.
Cover with a layer of soup and chicken mixture and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix and beat all together 4 minutes at medium speed. Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: That's sure to change the world?

title: easy beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add the beer and hand mix until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. "Smooth" tops with rubber spatula.
Bake for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan while warm and use a wire rack to cool.

title: cullen's bran muffins
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Put into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: carrot congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add orange and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate until almost set.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Pour into mold or flat dish.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients well together.
Pre-sift and gently fold in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes or until muffins are done in a well-greased pan. Optional:
1 cup of raisins.

title: butterscotch crunch
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot (not boiling) water. Remove from heat; add chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and let set until firm, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature for about 1 hour. Drain chicken.
Mash with fork.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, chicken and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry and salt. Mix to blend well.
Add onions and stir to blend.
Chill for 1 hour for flavors to blend.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; put in casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar and cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Twenty-four hours before needed:
Mix citrus juice as directed.
Pour into jello mold to create a decorative (and flavorful) frozen ring.

title: pizza dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Let it set while you mix the Dream Whip, milk and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy and then mix the Philly and powdered sugar mixture together.

title: crisp bacon
directions: Add the flour to the bacon.
Put in skillet and fry until crisp or brown.
Let set for 2 minutes, then it's ready to eat. (Notice the bacon is still the same size.)

title: black forest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: family's favorite chicken
directions: In casserole dish, layer cream of chicken soup, chicken breast (cut up into fingers), mushrooms and cheese slices.
Melt margarine and add to bread stuffing, then top off casserole with stuffing.
Pour apple juice on top of everything.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: brandy balls
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine milk and chocolate pieces.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add crushed wafers, sugar, 1/2 cup pecans and brandy, mixing well.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.

title: cherry fudge
directions: Grease 10 1/2 x 8-inch pan or dish with butter or oleo.

title: ribs with tortillas
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, brown sausage pieces, onion and garlic; remove from pan.
Drain off fat.
In same pan, brown the ribs, half at a time.
Return sausage mixture and ribs to pan.
Add undrained tomatoes, bouillon granules, green chili peppers, oregano and 1 cup of water.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Add zucchini and pepper pieces.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes more or until vegetables and ribs are tender.
Remove meats and vegetables to platter; keep warm.
Skim off fat from pan juices; measure juices. Add water if necessary to make 2 cups liquid; return to pan.
Blend 1/3 cup cold water into the flour; stir into liquid.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Pour some sauce over meat on platter; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Pass remaining sauce and warm tortillas.
Serves 8.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process on mix until thoroughly blended.
Pour over cooked, thinly sliced beef or pork. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Add 1/3 cup milk, flour and pinch of salt and pepper; beat until smooth.
Add remaining 2/3 cup milk; beat until smooth.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt butter in large, deep iron skillet.
Pour batter into skillet; place pan in oven for 45 to 60 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with roast beef or your favorite dish.

title: cucumbers in cream
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Place in bowl and sprinkle salt over them.
Refrigerate 15 minutes and then squeeze to drain off the liquid.
Add remaining ingredients, folding them gently.

title: chocolate almond coffee
directions: Place coffee and nutmeg in blender.
Add extracts while running machine.
Stop and scrape sides.
Process 10 seconds or longer.
Place mix in a bowl and stir in almonds.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yield:
Mix for 8 six-ounce servings.

title: devils food cupcakes
directions: Mix together warm water, cocoa and shortening and cool. Then in a mixing bowl, sift flour, salt, sugar, baking soda and baking powder. Add the cocoa mixture and beat well. Add eggs and vanilla, and beat again. Put paper baking cups in muffin pans. Fill each half full. Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: butterscotch marble cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 10-inch fluted tube pan; set aside. Preheat oven at 325°.
In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil and eggs; mix well.
Fold into fluted tube pan; distribute evenly.
Drizzle chocolate flavored syrup in swirling motions over cake mixture.
Place in oven.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool, then sprinkle your desired amount of sifted powdered sugar over top of cake.

title: chocolate or coconut microwave pie
directions: Scald milk in microwave for 10 minutes.
In meantime, mix dry ingredients; add egg yolks and margarine.
Add enough milk to make a smooth paste.
Then add rest of milk; beat smooth with mixer. Put in microwave for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove every 3 to 5 minutes and beat with mixer until smooth and thick.
Add coconut (if applicable); pour in pie shell.
Make meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: mustard-orange pork chops
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil pork chops 6 minutes.
Turn and broil 2 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 of glaze on chops.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes until no longer pink.
Serve pork chops with rest of glaze poured over them.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple crunch salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and cinnamon; chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts. Spoon into a 6-cup mold or bowl.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles.
Cook onions, mushrooms and garlic 5 minutes in nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in spinach, oregano, basil and pepper.
Set aside.
In food processor, blend cottage cheese, egg whites, flour and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese until smooth.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Place ground meat, salt and pepper in pan and beat until meat juices are absorbed.
Add chopped onions, garlic and butter.
Brown well.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomato sauce, parsley, rice and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer until liquid is almost absorbed.
Stem and seed peppers.
Remove inner membrane.
Rinse and fill with meat mixture, cover with stem end of pepper, place in baking pan with 1 cup water, remaining tomato sauce and pieces of butter.
Bake in oven at 350° about 1 hour, turning peppers on sides if necessary.

title: chinese cabbage soup
directions: Combine chicken and chicken broth; bring to boiling.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook only 3 to 4 minutes or just until cabbage is crisp-tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press one can crescent roll dough in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage and put on top of rolls. Put 1 package of cheese on top of sausage.
Press other can of rolls on top.
Bake according to directions on can.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a buttered pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
I like to serve this with a cream sauce over it, or diluted cream of mushroom soup with peas.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush 1/2 clove of the garlic and combine it in a jar with the salad oil.
Cover the jar and refrigerate the garlic oil at least 1 hour.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the garlic oil in a medium skillet. Add the bread cubes and saute them until they are browned, stirring often, and set them aside.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar gradually. Beat until mixture is fluffy. Add sifted dry ingredients. Add oil and vanilla. Fold in thin apple slices. Turn into greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, then mash.
Combine all ingredients. Bake for 15 minutes at 350° in buttered medium casserole dish.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan (flour bottom) for 30 to 40 minutes.
It will be quite brown on top.

title: cheese dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/2 beans, 1/3 sauce and add cream cheese (softened in microwave).
Add 1/2 the beans, 1/3 sauce, 4 ounces Cheddar, 4 ounces Mozzarella, 1/3 sauce, 4 ounces Cheddar and 4 ounces Mozzarella.
Microwave until cheese melts, 5 minutes or longer.

title: garden special
directions: Dice peppers, onions and celery.
Add water and cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes which have been peeled and cut up and seasoned.
Bring to a boil.
Put in hot jars and process 25 minutes for pints and 35 minutes for quarts.
Makes 10 pints.

title: baked fish stew
directions: Place fish in
baking
dish.
Season
fish fillets with salt and pepper.
Saute
vegetables
in
butter
and pour over fish. Bake in 350° oven
for
15 minutes or until fish flakes easily. Pour tomatoes overall and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and flour.
In the meantime, you have melted the margarine in a saucepan with the milk which you bring just to a boil.
Add to the batter hot.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Bake at 325° in a tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter and chocolate fudge
directions: In
heavy
saucepan,
over
low
heat,	melt chips with sweetened
condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread into well-greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill
hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store in airtight container at room temperature or in refrigerator.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute onion and 1/2 teaspoon minced garlic with sherry and 4 teaspoons Sauterne wine until dry.
Add margarine; stir in flour and spices.
Cook and stir 15 minutes.
Slowly stir in water, use whisk; blend.
Add bouillon and cook to dissolve.
Add half and half and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Cook peeled and deveined shrimp in a large skillet with 2 tablespoons butter, 2 teaspoons garlic and chopped shallots until shrimp turns pink.
Add 1/4 cup Sauterne wine, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Cook rice according to directions; serve the mixture over the rice.

title: vanilla, butter and nut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together.
Roll dough, with rolling pin, between 2 sheets of waxed paper until thick like pie crust about 10 X 12 inches.
Cover with 1/4 inch pats of margarine (1 1/2 sticks).
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Cream margarine, crisco and sugar together.
Add Eggs.
Combine milk and water.
Add alternately with flour.
Stir in flavoring.

title: pizza-bread sandwiches
directions: Slice the bread lengthwise.
Spread the spaghetti or pizza sauce on both halves (I like the sauce kind of thick.)
Be sure to cover the whole area of the bread; if you miss the edges, they will burn.
Place the mushrooms next to the sauce and then the pepperoni, olives or anything else you like on your pizza on top of the mushrooms.
Lightly season with the oregano and salt.
Sprinkle on the cheese until the toppings are covered.
Place on a cookie sheet and put in the oven on a lower shelf.
Broil at 300° for about 10 minutes or until the cheese is melted and barely starting to turn brown.
Serves 1 if you like big sandwiches or 10 if you use for hors d'oeuvres.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use for marinating poultry.
Baste with marinade while cooking.
Yields 1 3/4 cups plus 2 tablespoons.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion. Mix with other ingredients; cover with noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine biscuit mix, milk, cheese and 3 tablespoons margarine.
Drop by spoonfuls onto slightly greased cookie pan.
Bake for 8 or 10 minutes, or until brown.
Mix 2 tablespoons margarine and the garlic powder.
Brush over hot biscuits before removing from pan.
Eat while hot.

title: sauteed cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters, removing outer dark green leaves and core.
Rinse cabbage with cold water and drain.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add damp cabbage and toss to coat.
Add salt, pepper and seasoning salt. Cover skillet and simmer 7 to 10 minutes or until
crisp-tender.
Add extra flavor by adding 3 to 4 slices of bacon, chopped, to butter and cook until done.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook the whole cauliflower in boiling salt water for about 20 minutes. Drain and place in baking dish.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a plate.
Mix drained crab meat with 1/2 jar of cocktail sauce.
Spread over cream cheese. Pour remaining cocktail sauce over top and serve with crackers.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and flour with baking powder, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° until it springs back.

title: easter bread
directions: Into a large mixing bowl, measure water (use cool to lukewarm for compressed yeast).
Sprinkle or crumble yeast into bowl; stir until yeast dissolves.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour all at once.
Stir until smooth.
Cover bowl and let stand in warm place for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gramma's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil with a teaspoon of baking soda until tender.
Drain.
Place in cooker with other ingredients. Add fresh water, just to cover.
Simmer about 6 hours, stirring and adding water as needed.
When nearly done, taste for saltiness and sweetness.
Correct sweetness with sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: potatoes with creamy chicken and peas
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork.
Arrange in a circle on paper towels.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, turning and rearranging potatoes halfway through cooking time. Cover and set aside.

title: chop soupy
directions: Brown
meat
in
oil in skillet.
Add vegetables, soup, etc. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until meat is tender on low heat. Blend
the
cornstarch
and
cup of water; stir in sauce. Serve on rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with taco sauce, green chilies and onion.
Mix mushroom and Cheddar cheese soups with sour cream in a separate bowl.
Put a spoonful of the meat mixture and a spoonful of the soup mixture and shredded cheese in each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas and place in Pyrex dish.
Pour the remaining soup mixture and meat, if any left, over the top.
Add the rest of your shredded cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool and pick from bone.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Combine soups in a bowl.
Do not dilute.
In a glass casserole dish, first layer of chicken, next layer of stuffing, then layer of soup mixture.
Repeat until you have 3 layers and end with soup mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour or until top is lightly browned.

title: walnut raisin cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl,
combine
sugar
and	margarine.
Using
a wooden spoon, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift the flour, soda, powder and cinnamon.
Stir
into
egg mixture alternating with milk. Stir
in apples, nuts and raisins.	Pour into pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool and frost, if desired.

title: baked ice cream cones
directions: Prepare cake mix. Fill each cone 2/3 full.
Bake as cupcakes on cookie sheet or sit in cupcake pan.
Let cool.
Frost and put cherries on top of each cone.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice 1 banana in each pie crust.
Beat 1 (8 ounce) cream cheese with sugar and mix with Cool Whip.
Pour over bananas and top with pie filling.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender and drain.
Add all other ingredients except oleo and crackers.
Pour into dish; top with crackers.
Pour oleo over crackers.

title: french toast with cream cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread margarine into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Put in oven to melt.
Remove from oven.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and nutmeg.
Dip bread into egg mixture to coat all sides well.
Place in jelly roll pan; bake 7 minutes at 375°.
Turn and bake 7 more minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle toast with powdered sugar; serve with strawberry jam.

title: chicken or turkey gourmet holiday casserole
directions: Cream butter, flour, salt, thyme, nutmeg and milk.
Add bouillon cube and cheeses.
Cook hearts if frozen; drain and put in a 2-quart buttered shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Add chicken and mushrooms.
Pour cream sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hot cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until creamy.
Then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread in pie dish and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with party rye rounds.

title: boiled mayonnaise dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook 10 minutes.
Great over fruit salad.

title: mother's best ever pudding
directions: Mix in order listed.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1 cup brown sugar and pour 1 cup boiling water over it.
Stir until all sugar is dissolved.
Drop batter into liquid by spoonfuls.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Pour bottle of Woody's Cook-in sauce and bottle of Worcestershire over brisket.
Wrap in heavy foil.
Cook at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Easy and delicious!
Needs no salt or pepper.

title: tuna tarts(low-fat)
directions: Drain and flake a can of tuna.
In a medium bowl mix tuna, egg substitute, sour cream, mustard and oregano.
Coat a 2-cup casserole dish with Pam.
Add the bread crumbs and swirl to coat the dish evenly; add the tuna mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until mixture is set.
Makes 2 servings.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add escarole, and simmer, while you prepare meatballs.
Combine pork, garlic, shallots, parsley, and egg yolk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Form into 3/4 inch meatballs.
Drop the meatballs into the broth and continue to simmer 10 - 15 minutes.
Add Pastina and season to taste.
Turn off heat.
Begin to stir the soup clockwise and slowly drizzle in the beaten egg.
Serves 6.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions a short time until just tender.
Drain.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make small balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: lime butter chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute chicken until lightly brown on both sides. Cook until no longer pink and fork inserts easily.
Remove chicken from skillet and keep warm.
Drain and discard oil.
Add lime juice to same skillet.
Cook over low heat until juice bubbles.
Add butter and stir until it becomes opaque.
Stir in chives and dill. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve over rice.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating at low speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, stirring well.
Add flour and cocoa, stirring well.
Stir in pecans.
Chill dough 2 hours or until firm.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together.
Pour into large 10 x 13-inch loaf cake pan.
Chill until set.
Cover with bottom mix. Get cheese to room temperature.
Add the sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Put on top of the Jell-O mix.
Add crushed nuts and/or cherries to decorate.
Makes a very large salad and is very good.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs.
Heat all other ingredients and pour over browned spareribs.
Cover and roast 1 1/2 hours at 350° or low heat on top of stove.
Add more water if sauce becomes too dry. You can bake them in a crock-pot.

title: pepper steak(microwave)
directions: Set power select at Medium-high.
In oblong baking dish, heat oil 2 minutes.
Add steak, soy sauce and ginger.
Heat 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once.
Season with salt and stir in peppers and onions.
Set power select at High, covered 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in cornstarch blended with broth and heat 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until sauce is thickened, stirring once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Brown onion and ground beef; drain.
Add water and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Add parsley flakes, Italian seasoning and macaroni.
Cook until macaroni becomes tender.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli on bottom of 4-quart casserole.
Add chicken; mix with broccoli.
Combine soup and mayonnaise; spread on top of broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and 1 can French fried onions, if desired.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered for last 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: banana bonanza ice cream
directions: Puree bananas in blender (1 cup).
In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Beat in pureed bananas.
Stir in milk and cream.
Cover; refrigerate 2 to 3 hours to develop flavor.
Pour into ice cream freezer can.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: apecian carrots
directions: Clean the carrots.
Preheat oven to 250°.
In a skillet, cook the carrots in the wine and enough water to cover.
Boil the carrots until tender.
Remove carrots to a shallow baking dish. Combine the Worcestershire, butter and brown sugar.
Pour over the carrots and turn to coat. Bake for 15 minutes. Serves 10 to 15 people.

title: pork tenderloin medallions
directions: Trim tenderloin.
Cut into medallions about 1/2 inch thick. Flatten medallions with a meat mallet.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown
meat,
celery
and
onion
in 2 tablespoons fat. Cook the
noodles.
Mix noodles, soups, meat, celery and onion together.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut up stuffed olives and sprinkle
on
top.
Pour
some of the olive juice over top and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: taco dip
directions: Peel avocados; put in blender (no core).
Squirt lemon juice and mix.
Will be like paste.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Place 1 frozen strawberry in each compartment of an ice cube tray.
Top with the diluted grape juice and freeze.
At serving time, mix apple juice and ice cubes in a clear bowl.
Serves 6.

title: swiss steaks
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pour into meat.
Brown onions lightly in hot shortening in large skillet.
Brown meat.
Place onions on top of meat.
Add tomato and pizza sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.
Serve sauce with meat. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad cream puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on bed of lettuce with crackers of your choice.

title: chicken and mushroom dijon
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides; remove.
In remaining tablespoon hot margarine, cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid evaporates, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and mustard; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover, cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4.
