title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Pour oil from one jar of artichokes into frying pan and saute onion.
Drain other jar.
Chop artichokes into small bits and combine with other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Serve hot or cold.

title: dilled pork roast
directions: Cut about five deep slits across top of roast. Combine seasonings; stuff some into the slits. Tie meat securely. Rub roast with the remaining seasonings. Place in a large resealable plastic bag and refrigerate overnight. Remove roast from bag and place in a greased roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2
to 3 hours or until a meat thermometer reads 160°-170°. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until just tender. With 1 teaspoon sugar, mash well. Add other ingredients and top with the other 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix and shape into rolls.
Chill or freeze.
Slice in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: holiday relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
This is a very colorful dish and a delightful change from ordinary cranberry sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: creamed corn from beckham place, pasadena
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 2 and bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour; add to the corn.
Mix well and remove from heat.

title: cheerio nuggets
directions: Mix Cheerios, peanuts and raisins together in 4-quart greased bowl.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cube potatoes and onion.
Cook in water until tender.
Add corn and bring to a boil.
Mash slightly.
Heat milk and add to veggies. Add a large lump of butter and serve.
(Bit of smoked sausage may be added for flavor.)

title: pie crust
directions: Mix lard and flour until it crumbles, then add cold water. Make ball.
Roll out on floured table or board.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: swiss cream of vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan, mix vegetables, broth and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Divide mixture in 1/2.
Blend both halves and return to saucepan.
Stir in milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: mami eisenhower's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts in a mixing bowl.
Pour syrup over chocolate and beat until chocolate is melted.
Turn into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Cool several hours or until firm.
Cut into squares and store in an airtight container.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: raphael chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of roasting pan with chicken.
Combine soup, milk and wine; cover chicken evenly. Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and bake for another 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and place cheeses evenly over mixture. Bake until cheese is melted and golden brown (approximately 15 minutes).

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour. 15 minutes.
Or form into a ball and put on a rack to cook.
Fat drips away.
Check after about 1 hour and pour barbecue sauce over top. Bake another 15 minutes.

title: merry cranberry punch
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the orange slices. Chill until ready to serve.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer.
Fill cups 2/3 full.

title: mom's ice cream
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Slowly add sugar.
(Leave some sugar to mix in with yolks.)
Beat well.
In other bowl beat yolks, sugar, Pet milk, vanilla and salt.
Fold into egg whites.
Mix well.
Add fruit.
Pour into container and add milk.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and Miracle Whip.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipping cream. Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 2 hours before serving.
Serve sliced.

title: jumbo banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add mashed bananas and next 3 ingredients, beating until well blended. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture, stirring just until blended. Stir in pecans and 1 cup chocolate morsels. Spoon into greased jumbo muffin pans, filling 1/2 full. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and let cool completely on a wire rack. Drizzle with melted chocolate morsels if desired. Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: banana split
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: super junk sundae
directions: Put a pint of your favorite ice cream in a bowl.
Squirt with desired amount of whipped cream.
Then add marshmallows.
Top with M&M's and Hershey's chips.
Then sprinkle with nuts.
Then top it off with a juicy cherry.

title: bread
directions: Pour together warm water and dry yeast, but do not mix.
Cream together oleo, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir yeast mixture and add to oleo, sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir in warm water.
Add approximately 7 cups flour.
It will be slightly sticky.
Let rise to double its size.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix shrimp, scallops, green pepper, mushrooms, lemon and onion in rectangular baking dish.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, tarragon and bay leaf.
Pour over shrimp mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours, spooning marinade over shrimp mixture occasionally. Remove bay leaf.
Add lettuce and parsley to shrimp mixture.
Toss salad.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: brazilian banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Blend well.
Add flour with bananas, alternately, beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts. Pour into prepared pan and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesed zucchini casserole
directions: Sprinkle crackers into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer zucchini, tomatoes and onion over crackers.
Add seasoning.
Top with cheese and then bacon.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: jamaica cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, eggs, oil, flour, salt, pineapple, bananas, pecans, soda and cinnamon together.
Pour in cake pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix oleo, cream cheese, vanilla, powdered sugar and nuts.
Frost cake when cool.

title: quick and easy strawberry dessert
directions: Buy a small angel food cake and break into small pieces, then place in bottom of long glass pan.
Place Jell-O in boiling water. Place frozen strawberries into the hot Jell-O mixture and pour over the cake pieces while still hot.
Place in refrigerator until Jell-O sets.
Spread Cool Whip or whipped cream on top.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Mix meat, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, spices and tomato paste.
Spoon evenly over top.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over pie pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes at 400°. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: tuna dinner
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as shown on box.
Mix in soup and milk, then gently stir in tuna and peas.
Heat and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide everything in half.
Crumble half of sheet cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread half of pudding over cake crumbs. Add half of other ingredients in order given.
Repeat for second layer.
Garnish with nuts, cherries or strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: prairie fire dip
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.
Heat until the cheese melts thoroughly.
Serve in warming dish.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease and flour pan (Bundt 10-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Test at end of 1 hour.

title: jamie's enchiladas bake
directions: Brown hamburger and sprinkle with chili seasoning.
(Drain.) Crush 1/2 of the Doritos and put in a 10 x 12-inch baking dish. Layer meat, beans, tomatoes, mushroom soup, the rest of the Doritos and cheese.
Bake approximately 15 or 20 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and let cool.
Cut up all vegetables; add to noodles.
Pour dressing over mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Let chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cheese rings
directions: Sift flour, salt and red pepper.
Mix with cheese and margarine.
Put into cookie press and make rings.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots.
Add crushed pineapple and raisins.
Mix salad dressing, pineapple juice and sugar; add to carrot mixture.
If too dry, add more salad dressing.

title: orange cranberry relish
directions: Remove seeds from oranges.
Grind oranges and cranberries in grinder.
Add sugar.
Mix well; chill.
Add more sugar if you like it sweeter.
Will keep 4 to 6 weeks, refrigerated.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Combine coconut, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar.
Mix with egg whites.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with whipped topping.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: In heavy skillet, brown chicken in 4 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle 1/2 cup wine over chicken; cover and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Blend flour and shortening with fork, then slowly add water and mix well.
Knead 5 times with hands and form a ball.
Roll out on well-floured board.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients well.
Split each pan of rolls, leaving the bottoms in pan.
Spread the bottom with mixture, then put a layer of ham and cheese last.
Return tops.
Return the pan to plastic bag and refrigerate until ready to use.
Heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
May also be frozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops, no flour.
Wash rice; put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Lay pork chops on rice.
Pour off grease in pan and add beef broth plus 2 bouillon cubes and 1/2 can water. Dissolve cubes, then pour over chops and rice.
Cover with foil wrap and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli stuffed shells
directions: In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, broccoli, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons into each shell.
In 3 quart oblong baking dish, spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce.
Arrange stuffed shells in single layer in sauce.
Pour remaining 2 cups spaghetti sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
If desired, garnish with fresh sage.

title: molded cranberry and orange salad
directions: Wash and dry cranberries and oranges.
Peel the oranges, removing white membrane and seeds, then dice and add the sweetener.
Put the cranberries and 1 orange peel through the coarse blade of a food chopper.
Sprinkle the gelatin on the cold water to soften.
Dissolve the softened gelatin in boiling water and cool.
Add the cranberries and oranges to the gelatin and pour into molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.
Serves 6.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange.

title: ole's giant popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tins.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in milk and melted butter.
At low speed, add flour and salt.
Bake for 45 minutes until almost done. Slit the top and bake 10 more minutes.
Makes 1 dozen large or 2 dozen small.

title: okra-bacon salad
directions: Mix together bacon, okra, onions and green peppers in a large salad bowl.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently.

title: fresh blender lemonade
directions: For each serving:
Place 2 lemons, Simple Syrup and water in a blender with top on and blend at medium speed until lemons are liquified.
Add ice and blend on high until pureed (3 to 4 minutes).
Recipe can be adjusted to your personal preferences for sweetness or tartness.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shells. Chill or freeze.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt butter; mix cinnamon and salt with sugar.
Add to melted butter and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start at 400° and then decrease heat to 350°.
Bake until apples are tender.

title: focaccia
directions: Mix water, sugar, and yeast; let yeast dissolve. In mixer: mix together olive oil and salt; add yeast mixture; add 3 cups flour.

title: seafoam cake
directions: Beat egg whites 1/2 stiff; add cream of tartar.
Beat stiff. Add sugar, then add yellows one at a time.
Lastly, add the flour and vanilla.
Bake slowly for 35 to 50 minutes.
This cake can be iced or cut in squares and covered with whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together 3 times.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and applesauce alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 (8 x 8-inch) cake.

title: high fiber bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Stir in the oats, bran cereal and fruit.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and molasses.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon the batter into greased muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes about 20 muffins, with 130 calories each.
Leftover muffins can be frozen and reheated in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: In bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; break up and stir in cranberry sauce and add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Set in 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Especially good with turkey or ham.
Serves 12 or 14.

title: pineapple appetizers
directions: Wash pineapple thoroughly.
Cut off the top of pineapple and save to use as a garnish.
Slice pineapple into 4 sections.
Slice the pineapple away from skin.
Cut down center and then into individual pieces.
Slice cherries in half and cut cream cheese into small pieces.
Place cherry on a piece of cream cheese and attach to pineapple sections with a toothpick.
Place on a tray and use for garnish in the middle.

title: creamy tuna spread
directions: Reserve 8 center egg slices for garnish; chop remaining eggs. Stir cream cheese until softened; add chopped eggs, tuna, onion, 2 tablespoons chopped parsley, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Mix until blended.
Divide mixture into 2 balls.
Roll in parsley.
Garnish bottom edge with egg slices, cut in half.
Makes 4 cups.
You can cut this recipe in half for 1 ball.

title: garlic spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine.
Mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; chill.

title: bite size pizzas
directions: Grease 10 holes on muffin tins.
Put one biscuit in each hole. Shape biscuits to inside of cup.
Place 1 tablespoon pizza sauce into each biscuit.
Fill each biscuit with desired amounts of meat, onion, black olives and cheeses.
Bake at 350° until outer edge of crust is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool 5 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all dressing ingredients together.
Add dressing to cabbage to your taste.
Yields 1 gallon of dressing.

title: pasta vegie salad
directions: Toss all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Toss again before serving.

title: mandarin orange muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg and flavoring and mix at medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl before and after each addition.
Stir dry ingredients to blend and add along with water to egg mixture.
Mix at medium speed until flour is absorbed.
Stir mandarin oranges into batter.
Fill the paper lined cups half way.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes and lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with salad dressing.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Measure flour and sift it. Cream butter well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add sifted flour, baking soda and salt alternately with sour cream. Use 1 or 2 teaspoons of any flavoring that you like; lemon and vanilla are especially good. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Cream all ingredients by hand.
Roll into small balls, then roll into cinnamon.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix well and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kraut cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, alternating with water.
Stir in kraut.
Bake in two 9-inch round tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: italian chicken gizzards
directions: Slice up the gizzard into a skillet.
Add water to cover the gizzards.
Cover and let the water come to a boil.
Remove from the heat and drain in a colander.
Add enough olive oil to the skillet so that the gizzards do not stick to the bottom.
Heat the oil; add the gizzards, garlic and onion.
When the gizzards start to fry, add more olive oil.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, parsley and garlic powder.
Add the mushrooms and gravy mix.
Cook until the gizzards are chewable, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves five.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat shortening in a large skillet; brown chicken on all sides and remove from skillet. Sprinkle flour
into fat remaining in skillet.
Cook stirring constantly, until
the mixture turns light brown.
Do not let burn.
Return
the
chicken
with the sausage, onions, green pepper,
tomatoes
and
garlic.
Cook,
stirring
gently about 10 minutes.
Stir in the water, thyme, salt, red pepper, seasoning and rice.
Bring
to
boiling and lower heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir
in
shrimp;
simmer
15 minutes more.
Stir in parsley
and
green onions and simmer 5 minutes longer until rice is tender.

title: curried asparagus soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, place the asparagus, broth and greens and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer slowly for 12 to 15 minutes or until the vegetables are very tender.
Place the mixture in a food processor or blender and add the lemon juice and seasonings.
Puree until smooth.
Serve hot immediately or chill.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add roll oats; mix well.
Bake at 350° until tested, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook macaroni.
Mix hamburger and onion with macaroni and pizza sauce.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with Mozzarella cheese and then pepperoni.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine coffee, milk, vanilla and sugar; stir well.
Chill thoroughly.
Place ice cream in punch bowl.
Pour coffee mixture over ice cream, stirring gently.
Top with droplet of whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Whip cream.
Cream the cheese; blend with whipped cream and pineapple.
When Jell-O mixture is slightly set, add creamed mixture.
Pour into molds and chill until firm.
Garnish with cherries.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well.
Bake at 325° according to cake mix directions on box.

title: another cookie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use imagination.
Make plain or add your favorite nuts, chocolate chips, or so forth.

title: dill weed crackers
directions: Put oyster crackers in airtight container.
Mix the first four ingredients together and pour on the oyster crackers.
Shake well and store overnight.

title: grilled szechuan chicken salad
directions: Lightly sprinkle both sides of boneless, skinless chicken with seasoned pepper.
Grill; slice into strips.

title: orange beets
directions: Drain beets and set aside.
In small pan, mix butter, sugar, cornstarch and orange juice.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add beets and continue cooking until beets are hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce.
Mix well to dissolve sauce.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Place in oiled mold or pan and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in milk and banana. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend together; add nuts.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: beat and bake cocoa cake(no eggs)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add salad oil, vinegar, vanilla and water; mix until smooth.
Then add 1/2 cup additional cold water and mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and frost.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven until firm.

title: "tootie" bread
directions: Partially slice the bread into 16 pieces.
Cut each slice of cheese diagonally and place 1 triangle of cheese in between each piece of bread.
Place bread on a foil covered cookie sheet. Combine butter, onion, mustard and poppy seed; mix well.
Put mixture on bread on top and sides (like icing a cake).
Place small pieces of bacon on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes on 350° and serve hot.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend with electric mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until brown.
(May top with whipped cream.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour juice off all fruit.
Layer fruits, coconut and cherries to garnish.
Add additional juice if mixture seems too dry. Refrigerate.
Add mint, if desired.

title: shrimp boat dip
directions: Hollow out one loaf of bread.
Break apart or cut the removed part and second loaf of bread into bite size pieces.
Combine mayo, cheese, crab and onion in baking dish.
This step can be done ahead and refrigerated until needed.
Bake dip mixture at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until hot).
Pour into hollowed out bread. Serve surrounded by bread pieces for dipping.

title: cream puffs
directions: In large saucepan, heat water and margarine to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once.
Continue beating by hand until smooth.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls, about 3-inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut off tops and scrape out soft "stuff".

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17 minutes.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Form into small balls.

title: stacey's yummy yorkshire pudding
directions: Blend together.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Heat oven to 425°.
Put 1/4 cup cooking oil in pan and heat for 10 minutes. Pour cold batter into heated pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry torte with sauce
directions: Preheat oven
to
With electric mixer, blend the margarine and
powdered
sugar,
then
beat in 1 cup of flour. Press the batter into pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until a toothpick
inserted in center comes out clean.
Set aside to cool. When
crust
has
cooled,
spoon raspberries over baked crust and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Reserve raspberry juice for sauce.

title: beef empanadas
directions: Brown ground beef with ingredients except corn flour.
Cook for 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables and cheese.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Melt butter and crackers.
Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown onion and meat
in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased
casserole.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Spread
with cornbread batter.
Bake, uncovered, in hot oven at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Beat very well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Separate rolls to make 4 flats of dough by pinching perforations together.
Spread mixture on dough and roll in jellyroll fashion.
Cut in 1/2 inch slices and spread on lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Use with grilled chicken strips.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix with blender, eggs, milk and vanilla; set aside.
Over low flame, mix sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Once melted well, mix in egg and milk mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool completely before serving.
Great with Cool Whip on top.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine hash browns, onion, chicken broth and water in Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with shredded cheese, cooked diced ham or bacon bits, if desired.

title: sauce for fruit salad
directions: Cook, stirring all the time, until it begins to thicken.
Turn off as soon as it starts to boil.
Let cool and pour over fruit.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy Kisses in a large bowl. Mix on low speed until dough forms together.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut and roll each one in sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Top each cookie with a candy Kiss and press on firmly.
Cookie will crack around edge.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine mushroom soup, mayonnaise, beaten egg and onion.
Combine this sauce with broccoli; top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cherry blossom salad
directions: May add almond extract.

title: prune cake
directions: Flour the prunes so they don't clump together.
Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and prunes.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick inserted comes out dry.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in order given.
Mix until well blended.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 1 stick margarine.
Blend until smooth.
Pour evenly over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate.
Just before chocolate mixture is set, cut into squares.
Return to refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Wipe granules from side of pan.
Do not stir while cooking.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Pour into bowl and cool until firm.
Beat.
Roll into balls and cover with chopped nuts or add nuts to fudge and pour into square pan and cut into squares.

title: chicken pineapple skillet
directions: Over high heat saute chicken breasts which have been cut into strips.
Sprinkle with salt and stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Continue to cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple; reserve juice.
In bowl, mix pineapple juice, cornstarch, cinnamon and soy sauce.
Stir juice mixture into pan of chicken and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook just until clear.
Serve over hot rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Wash the zucchini; trim off ends, but do not peel.
Shred on medium blade of vegetable shredder.
Combine eggs with zucchini; add cheese, biscuit mix and seasoning.
Mix well.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Cream butter with all ingredients except shrimp.
Divide shrimp equally on 6 pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Top with butter mixture.
Bring foil up around shrimp; seal tightly.
Place shrimp directly on hot coals.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve in foil packages.
Serves 6.

title: banana pecan coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square pan. Mix pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Stir flour and sugar until well mixed.
Combine bananas, eggs, oil and vanilla until blended.
Add blended liquid ingredients to flour mixture and stir.
Spread half of batter into pan.
Sprinkle half of nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spread rest of batter.
Sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: holiday sparkle
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whir until blended. Garnish as desired. Makes 1 serving.

title: sweet and spicy mexican coffee
directions: Break each cinnamon stick into 2 or 3 pieces.
Place cinnamon and cloves in a tea ball or cheesecloth bag.
In a large saucepan, combine water, brown sugar and instant coffee.
Add tea ball. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Stir in vanilla.
Remove tea ball.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: old fashioned butter cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Pour in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Combine flour with soda and salt.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow cake to stand 5 minutes.
Finish cooling on a rack.
Dust with powdered sugar before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together then add the rest.
Mix until smooth.
Grease and flour 3 (1 lb.) coffee cans.
Fill each 1/2 full.
OR grease 6 mini loaf pans.	Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 14-day cucumber pickles
directions: Fill a 5-gallon crock 2/3 to 3/4 full of cucumbers.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saut onion, celery and pepper in oil until tender.
Place in roasting pan.
Spread 2 cups uncooked rice over vegetables.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Place chicken pieces on top and season with garlic powder and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast or beef dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in covered Dutch oven at 250° for 5 hours.

title: surfer squares
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces, sugar and butter in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars; makes about 24 bars.

title: gummy cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown and white sugars well.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring, nuts (optional) and gumdrops.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: "thangs"
directions: Line jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) with graham crackers. Bring to boil sugar and margarine, and boil for 2 minutes.
Add pecans.
Immediately pour over graham crackers and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool, remove from pan and place on rack.
Tastes like a praline.

title: jeannie barnes poppy seed cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat all ingredients
10 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 55 minutes.
Will rise and settle.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Let cool completely before removing from pan.

title: cold curried chicken rice
directions: Cool rice. Marinate overnight (or several hours) in dressing. Add all other ingredients. Serve cold.
(Good with a fruit salad or baked apples and hot cheese bread.)

title: instant cocoa-amaretto mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container. Makes 4 1/3 cups.
Place 1/3 cup of mix in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.

title: martha washington balls
directions: In a double boiler, melt the paraffin and chocolate chips. Mix all other ingredients together.
Form into small balls. Insert a toothpick into each ball.
Chill them so they are firm and can be dipped into the melted paraffin and chocolate.
After dipping, put the balls on wax paper to cool.
Remove toothpicks and store in closed containers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Note:
Key limes are yellow and fresh ones are found only in South Florida.
Bottled juice from Key West may be found in some supermarkets.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine hash brown potatoes, sour cream, soup, cheese and onion in lightly greased casserole. Drizzle with melted butter and top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins until soft, but not mushy.
Peel and cut in half, lengthwise.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Mix salt, sugar and flour.
Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Pour cream over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zippy sweet and sour sauce
directions: In small sauce pan combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Mix well. Gradually stir in remaining ingredients, cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened. Stir frequently. Cool and cover. Store in refrigerator. Yield 1 1/2 cups.

title: country style meat loaf
directions: Soften bread in milk.
Add to meat together with egg, salt, pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and form into loaf.

title: alberta's ice cream cake
directions: Heat chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and milk over low heat until chips are melted.
Arrange the wafers around the sides and bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Slice ice cream; place over wafers.
Pour some sauce over ice cream.
Repeat a second layer. Cover and freeze.

title: every man's beef burgundy
directions: Cut steak into 1 inch cubes; sprinkle with meat tenderizer, following label directions.
In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, crumble and set aside.
Quickly brown meat in bacon fat; drain off excess fat.
Season meat to taste with salt and pepper.
Add broth, wine, water, garlic, bay leaf, and bacon.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Thicken liquid with thin flour and water paste to make gravy.
Serve with riced potatoes, hot noodles or rice.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: torte
directions: Place strips of waxed paper crisscross over bottom of 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans allowing ends to extend over sides of pan for easy removal of cake.

title: dinner salad italiano
directions: Make a big tossed salad from the lettuce, mushrooms, cucumber, onion, salami and Provolone.
Toss with bottled Italian or vinaigrette dressing, then add the sliced tomatoes and serve. Yield: 3 servings.

title: "no peek" beef stew
directions: Place in a Dutch oven; stir.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Do not peek!
Serve over rice or noodles.
(May cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low.)

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cream the margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add half of the sugar, beating well.
Add remaining sugar alternating with milk, beating until smooth enough to spread.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Kids love this on cupcakes.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients except sugar in a large mixing bowl. Make a well in center.
In another container, combine oil, eggs, sugar, pears and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 325°
oven for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Keep bread wrapped for freshness.
Can be frozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add fruit cocktail, Cool Whip and marshmallows and stir well.
Let chill in refrigerator until congealed.

title: leah bean's raisin and white cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk. Mix well after each addition.
Take out 2/3 of batter and place in separate bowl.
Add 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1 teaspoon cloves. Divide this batter between 2 greased and floured cake pans.
To remaining 1/3 batter, add 1 tablespoon molasses and 1/2 cup ground raisins.
Pour this batter into a third greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Frost this 3 layer cake with boiled frosting.

title: icebox pie
directions: Thaw lemonade, then mix milk and lemonade together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour ingredients into graham cracker crust and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Let rise until double.
Knead.
Let rise until double, then shape into loaves.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Melt margarine and blend in with sugar, cheese and extract. Mix well.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Prepare and slice potatoes in thin slices, about 4 cups.
Cook onion in margarine in a 2-quart pan until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Heat to boiling about 1 minute and remove from heat.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes and top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: bits 'o brickle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, mix Bits 'O Brickle with liquid shortening until evenly coated.
Then stir in 6 tablespoons flour until well coated.
Set aside.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except last 4.
Stir in beef, then add vegetables.
Cover and bake 3 hours, stirring twice in Dutch oven (5 to 6-quart).
Makes 8 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Loosely cover any leftovers.
Makes 24.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in a double boiler; let them melt. Add cracker crumbs, pecans and fruit.
Mix well and put in a buttered dish.
Press well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Beat in bananas. Gradually beat in dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries. Pour into 2 loaf pans (greased). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil in hot water cabbage leaves and drain.
Mix ground beef, salt, onion, rice and egg altogether just like you would meat loaf. Roll a portion of filling into a cabbage leaf and toothpick shut. Place in a square pan.
After filling all cabbage leaves and placing them in a pan, pour can of tomato soup over rolls plus 3/4 cup water.
Cover with foil and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add the V-8 juice.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Cut and serve on lettuce.
Top with Ranch dressing mixed with 1/4 cup of mayonnaise.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Wash, trim and dry spinach; refrigerate.
Toast sesame seed on pie pan in a preheated 350° oven, shaking once or twice, until golden, 10 to 12 minutes; cool.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, onions, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce in tightly covered container; shake until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Refrigerate.

title: crispy croutons
directions: Set power select at High.
In small glass bowl, heat butter 1 minute.
Brush butter onto bread (one side only); cut bread into small cubes.
In oblong baking dish, arrange bread; drizzle with remaining butter.
Heat 5 to 6 minutes or until bread is crispy, stirring twice.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Store uncovered until ready to serve.

title: delicious zucchini
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole. Cover.
Microwave on High 12 minutes, turning or stirring twice.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix ingredients together as listed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until tests done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put half of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover half with cheese; add rest of broccoli and cheese.

title: poison sandwiches
directions: Butter the sliced bread.
Make 4 cheese sandwiches and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over the sandwiches.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight (or at least 4 hours).

title: apple pie
directions: I cook my apples a little with the other ingredients until they are a little tender.
Pour all ingredients into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Add top crust, cut slits for steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for about 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well, preferably with electric mixer.
Add milk slowly.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Texture should be light and fluffy.
Fold in coconut, nuts and raisins; pour into 3-quart (2835-ml) buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° (177°C) for 30 to 45 minutes or until firm.
Place marshmallows on top and return to oven.
Increase temperature to 375° (190°C) and bake until marshmallows are golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: french bread sandwich rolls
directions: Unroll French bread onto cookie sheet.
Spread meat such as pepperoni or ham to cover.
Spread with cheese (mozzarella or American).
Roll back up and bake the time on the roll.
Pizza sauce can be added to the pepperoni rolls if desired.

title: favorite vegetable pickles
directions: Boil the vinegar, oil, sugar, pickling salt, water and alum together.
Put over vegetables in pint jar with dill on bottom and top.
Boil lids and seal.
Boil water in canner and put in jars. Cover.
Turn off heat and leave setting in canner overnight, covered.
Makes 2 to 3 pints.

title: fruity pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/8-inch thick and overlap in 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Combine cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread mixture over cookie dough.
Arrange various fruits over cheese mixture.
Mix marmalade and water together and spread over fruit.
Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: tricolor salad
directions: In saucepan, cook carrot in water to cover, plus one inch. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes.
Add potato; cook 10 minutes.
Add frozen peas the last 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add garbanzo beans; toss.

title: greg's all occasion salad("guests will be impressed")
directions: Keep fruit and vegetables separate.
Peel and slice kiwi. Slice strawberries.
Slice red onion.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into a ball.

title: apple crunch
directions: Fill pie tin half full of apples.
Cover with white sugar and cinnamon.
Mix brown sugar, butter, oats and flour.
Press mixture down on top of apples.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: In a very
large bowl, mix sugars with shortening.
Add vanilla and eggs;
mix
thoroughly.
Add
flour,
baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon;
mix well.
Fold in oatmeal, coconut and chocolate
chips.
Drop
by
teaspoon
on
greased baking sheet.
Bake 10
to	15 minutes in 350° oven.
Allow to cool for two minutes before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: stuffed carrots
directions: Cut carrots 3-inches from top, reserving smaller end for another use.
Cook carrots in a small amount of water for 20 minutes or until tender, but firm.
Let cool.
Scoop out the center of each carrot.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Place lemonade in pitcher or punch bowl; add ginger ale mix. Cut lemon into thin slices.
Add lemons and raspberries to lemonade mixture.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Put nuts in pan and let warm while oven is pre-heating.
Mix egg mixture until stiff. Take nuts out and melt butter in pan.
Add nuts to egg mixture. Bake for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Do not get nuts too brown or they will be dry.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add vegetable soup (do not add water) and drained corn.
Simmer.
Remove from heat; pour into baking dish and top with canned biscuits (or homemade ones).
Bake at 375° until biscuits are browned.
Remove from oven and serve. A one dish complete meal.

title: chocolate chip walnut pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients except pie shell until blended.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden and set but still moist.
Serve slender wedges.
Great with a cup of coffee or vanilla ice cream. Serves 10.

title: pakistani chicken(pilau)
directions: Mix chicken with next 7 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low to medium heat until chicken is done.
At the same time, cook rice according to directions on the package.

title: irish cream
directions: Place ingredients in a blender and blend for 2 minutes. Bottle and refrigerate.

title: omelettes
directions: Melt grease in skillet at medium setting.
In a bowl, beat the eggs and milk.
Pour batter in the skillet.
Let cook until golden brown on bottom side, then with a spatula, flip over and let cook on the other side.
Put cheese and onion on top and then fold in half.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in the package of dressing mix.
Blend in wine and golden mushroom soup.
Mix in cream cheese, and stir until smooth. Heat through, but do not boil.
Arrange chicken breast in a single layer in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake for 60 minutes in the preheated oven.
Twenty minutes before the chicken is done, bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Cook pasta until al dente, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Serve chicken and sauce over pasta.

title: play dough
directions: There are 2 basic formulas.
Use a white under eye makeup stick for good overall coverage.

title: caramel icing
directions: Let first 3 ingredients boil until thick, then add brown sugar.
Put caramel kisses in.
Let cake cool for 30 minutes and put the icing on your cake.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients except pecans.
Then stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon; remove.
Stir-fry clams in bacon grease.
Stir-fry carrots, onion and potatoes until done.
Add butter, if needed. Remove veggies.
Add butter to remaining bacon grease.
Add flour and spices.
Fry until golden.
Add 6 cups milk all at once; stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Do not boil.
Crumble in bacon and serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Spread in an 8 or 9-inch pastry-lined shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss together shredded cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle on meat.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: schaum tortes
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vinegar until stiff.
Add sugar very gradually, a teaspoon at a time.
Beat until mixture holds a stiff peak.
Add flavorings.
Cover baking sheet with brown paper.
Shape mixture with a spoon into uniform mounds.
Makes 8 small or 6 large meringues.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake at 225° for about 1 hour.
Remove from baking sheet.
Cool.
Serve with fresh fruit topping and ice cream.

title: crazy macaroni salad
directions: Heat water to boil, add macaroni and onion.
Cook until tender; drain and wash.
Cover with butter.
Add mushrooms, black olives, green chilies, relish, pimentos, boiled eggs and pineapple chunks.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Serve cold.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 1/2 cup.
Mix crumbs with butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 carton Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie crust. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Prepare pudding mix by package directions. Spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with rest of cookie crumbs.
Garnish with maraschino cherries (optional).

title: butterscotch chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Generously butter and flour a loaf pan.
Blend together butter and sugar in food processor, using plastic blade.
Add eggs and blend.
Add bananas and process until well mixed.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Serve while hot.
Serves 40.

title: frosty strawberry creme
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, nuts and margarine; spread evenly in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: san francisco rice
directions: *Place vermicelli in plastic bag and with rolling pin, crush to about the size of rice.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Drain liquid from peaches and save. In medium saucepan, boil peach juice, lemon jello, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves until dissolved. Add peaches and chill for 20 minutes. Stir in mandarin oranges with juice and crushed pineapple with juice. Pour in 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until set. Store in refrigerator. Serves 10 to 12.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Make jello per instructions.
Don't let set.
Mix all ingredients together and let set.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Then add milk and softened yeast.
Store in refrigerator until one hour before baking.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick and cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until light brown or about ten.
The nice thing about these biscuits is that you can store the dough in the refrigerator and make it up as needed.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: lo-cal blackberry shake
directions: Process in food processor or blender.
Serve with a meal or as a snack drink.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Peel, pit and coarsely mash peaches to measure 4 cups. Combine peaches, pectin and lemon juice in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in sugar and allspice; return to a boil, and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
Quickly ladle hot mixture into hot, sterilized jars, filling to 1/4 inch from top. Remove air bubbles; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Yields 6 half pints.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook to soft-ball stage (234°). Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into buttered pan.

title: cheese caraway batter bread
directions: In mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cheese, shortening, sugar, salt, caraway seed and 2 cups of the flour. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape batter from sides of bowl. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Stir down batter by beating about 25 strokes.
With floured hands, shape into loaf and put in greased pan.
Let rise again.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°. Brush with melted butter.

title: grandma's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks and flour together a little at a time and keep beating until flour and eggs are blended.
This makes a stiff dough.
Roll in little balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press with a fork fairly flat.
Spread with unbeaten egg whites.
Press on cherries or walnuts.
Bake about 8 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: candied christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 19 minutes.
Take up while warm.
Do not let brown much, just around the edges.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and eggs.
Mix soda and baking powder into flour.
Add flour and milk alternately to the other mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Chill dough and drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: elsie's chess pie for posterity
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Beat the two egg yolks and whole egg together.
Add vinegar and water.
Add gradually to flour, sugar and salt mixture.
Fold in butter and vanilla.
Beat well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with meringue and brown for about 12 minutes in a 360° oven.

title: sausage-mushroom souffle
directions: Layer the first 3 ingredients in order given in baking dish. Combine eggs with 2 1/2 cups of milk and seasonings in a bowl, mixing well.
Pour over sausage.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Combine soup with 1/3 soup can milk in small bowl, blending until smooth.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, beating well. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add this mixture and sour cream alternately to creamed eggs, butter and sugar.
Add banana, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Cook at 350° in two loaf pans until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: no bake drop cookies
directions: Combine in large saucepan first 4 ingredients; bring to rolling boil and cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: orange salad
directions: Peel oranges and divide into sections.
Place in a bowl and stir oranges, olive oil and black pepper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. This is great after a heavy meal!

title: shrimp sandwich spread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and lemon juice in mixer.
Add the other ingredients and mix by hand.
Season to taste.
Chill before spreading.
Butter bread before spreading with shrimp spread.
You may wish to cut bread with various shaped cookie cutters before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix the sugar, water, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pappardelle ala contadina
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Mince onions.
Remove sausage meat from casings and chop.
Put salted water on for pasta.

title: reeds' chocolate crunchies
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and margarine.
Add Rice Krispies. Roll into small balls and chill.
Melt bark in double boiler or melt in microwave.
Dip balls and put on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: grits spoon bread(shared by lib faulkner)
directions: Scald milk in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine grits, sugar and salt; stir into milk.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly, 4 to 5 minutes or until very thick.
Let cool; beat egg yolks and stir into mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into mixture.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
(Spoon in gently.)
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until slightly browned.
Serve hot with red eye gravy.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cut tomatoes, peppers and cheese into bite size pieces in large mixing bowl.
Add salami, pepperoni, onion, olives and pasta; stir to blend.

title: hash brown-ham casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream and soup.
Stir in frozen potatoes, ham, American cheese and onion.
Transfer mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread evenly.

title: laura's grilled shrimp and scallops
directions: Pure all ingredients in blender.
Alternate shrimp and scallops on skewers and place in shallow pan.
Pour marinade over and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Grill skewers on a barbecue, basting with remaining marinade.
Can be used to marinate other seafood or chicken.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate or chop ingredients together.
Cover with dressing.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Peel watermelon rind, removing green and pink portions; cut into cubes. Let rind stand overnight in saltwater; drain and rinse. Cover rind with cold water in saucepot; cook until soft.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay out 1 package of rolls; pinch seams together.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread mixture on rolls; top with other package of rolls.
Beat egg white until foamy; brush on top of rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top when done.
Good warm or cold.

title: favorite buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt. Combine eggs, milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: pudding cake
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and pecans. Mix, then press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: homemade soap
directions: Dissolve lye in 4 cups of water.
Add ammonia, Borax and sugar, previously dissolved in water.
Slowly pour lukewarm lye mixture into melted grease in a stone jar, stirring constantly until creamy.
Cover until cool enough to cut in bars.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
I usually make up 1/2 the recipe at a time and it makes that gallon jar full.
So the full recipe would make many cookies.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.

Stir in flour and 1 to 2 teaspoons salt. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil. Add broth, broccoli and carrots. Cook over low heat, don't boil, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes or until carrots are done-tender. Add pepper and salt to taste. Yields 2 quarts.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft and drain.
Add milk and beat thoroughly.
Season for taste.
Work butter into flour.
Add egg, milk, onion and grated carrot.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot milk.
Cover saucepan and cook about 10 minutes on medium heat. Add half and half; stir to blend.
Serves 4.
Double the recipe for 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all together and mix well.
Let set 30 minutes.
Shape in tablespoon.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: chicken roll-up
directions: Pound meat until thin.
Place slice of ham, cheese and tomato on each piece and roll up.
Secure with toothpick.

title: tid-tills' tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook for 2-3 hours or until desired thickness. Taste along the way and add more ingredients if needed. Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Simmer beans for 15 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients well and put into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until onion is tender.
Stir in rice, chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in beaten eggs and cook 3 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef tortilla pizza
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion; drain.
Add oregano and salt. Lightly brush tortilla with oil.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 3 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture evenly over toasted tortillas; top with tomato.
Sprinkle with basil and cheeses.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine mustard and jelly in a crock-pot.
Heat until jelly is melted.
Cut hot dogs in bite-size pieces and add to mixture. Cook on low about 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Render salt pork in saucepan.
Add onions.
Saute until brown. Add beef.
Cook until brown.
Sprinkle with flour, marjoram, thyme, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in wine and bouillon. Simmer for 4 to 5 hours.
Add mushrooms.
Cook for 45 minutes longer.
May reserve sauteed onions and add with mushrooms.
May bake in oven at 250° until done to taste.
Serve with hot noodles, rice or small potatoes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour (salt and soda if needed).
Stir in oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix oil, onion, garlic and seasoning in 10-inch skillet.
Over medium heat, cook until onion is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in spinach and cook until tender and liquid evaporates. Remove from heat and stir in mushroom soup, Parmesan cheese and egg.
In a medium bowl, stir spaghetti sauce and heavy cream together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Set remainder aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
In Dutch oven, heat Prego, tomato sauce, diced green pepper, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Cook pastas; drain and add to sauce.
Mix well.
Pour into a large glass dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spread cheese on top; bake for 5 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes before you cut.

title: salsa chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork and onion; cook 5 to 10 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, stirring frequently.
Stir in salsa and beans.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until pork is tender and flavors are blended, stirring occasionally.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Pour milk and apple juice over marshmallows and let stand 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Combine crushed vanilla wafers and gingersnaps, nuts, raisins, fruit and cherries in a large bowl. Add marshmallow mixture and mix well.
Pour into a foil lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover top with foil.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 days before slicing.
If desired, decorate with candied cherries and almonds.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Dissolve cocoa in 1/2 cup water; heat to a smooth paste.
Add to other ingredients, then add milk and vanilla.
Add soda with flour, which has been sifted 3 times; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: bread stuffing for 200 people
directions: Divide bread between two 10-gallon containers equally.
Divide other ingredients.
Mix, swish, mix and swish and mix until all bread (broken) is absorbed by moisture.
Taste and add dry ingredients if necessary.
Makes about 4 large pans (rectangle turkey roasters).
Bake approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Cover pans with foil for first 1 1/2 hours, then uncover to brown top.

title: california cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, almonds and sesame seeds. Whisk together vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar, oil and ramen seasoning. Just before serving, toss salad with broken noodles and dressing.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and corn in a greased casserole dish.
Mix together the sour cream, soup, salt, cheese and onion and spread on top of bean/corn mixture.
Melt the butter and mix in the crushed crackers and almonds.
Spread on top and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Can also be prepared the night before and refrigerated until you're ready to bake.

title: squash pancakes
directions: Note:
Depending on how watery the squash is you may need to add more flour/or more milk if to dry.
Should be on the thin side.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper.
Slice oranges; remove seeds and put rind and oranges through food chopper.
Mix with berries and sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator for a few hours before serving.
This can be put up for future use in sterilized glasses covered with paraffin.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, butter and oil until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick and easy coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Spread 1/2 of mixture into an 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: jaffa cheesecake slice
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 325 to 350°.
Brush a 9 inch square cake tin with oil or melted butter.
Line base with baking paper, extending over 2 sides.
Place flour, cocoa and confectioners sugar in a food processor; add butter using pulse action, process for 45 seconds until mixture comes together.
Press into prepared tin, smoothing surface with the back of a spoon.
Bake for 15 minutes; cool completely.
Reduce oven to moderately slow 325°.
To make topping, combine cream cheese, rind and sour cream in a large mixing bowl.
Using electric beaters, beat until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs, sugar and chocolate.
Pour topping over base.
Bake for about one hour or until set; cool completely in tin.
Serve, cut into squares, decorated with grated chocolate and glace orange.

title: cornbread
directions: Put oil in iron skillet; put skillet in oven while preheating to 375°.
Meanwhile, mix other ingredients in bowl.
When oven is heated, remove skillet; pour excess oil in cornbread mixture and mix.
Pour mix into skillet and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring cherries (undrained), water and sugar to a boil.
Pour in cherry jello.
Let cool.
Add Coke, crushed pineapple and walnuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Place 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon butter inside each apple.
Place 1 apple on each pastry square.
Fold dough to enclose apple, sealing edges.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bring remaining 1 cup sugar, margarine, cinnamon and water to a boil in saucepan.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting with pan juices every 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: the hot man crab
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine crab, 1/4 cup mayonnaise, relish and salt; spread on 4 toast slices.
Top with tomato slices.
Spread remaining toast with mayonnaise; place on tomatoes.
Cover each with 2 slices of cheese.
Bake 10 minutes, until hot.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: deviled english peas
directions: Spread peas evenly in a casserole dish.
Spread other ingredients evenly in order as listed.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in a small amount of butter.
Add soup and 3/4 can water.
In bottom of bowl, add large pieces of French bread. Pour soup mixture over bread.
Top with cheese.
Brown in oven.

title: poppy seed casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Crumble the crackers coarsely.
Melt butter.
Add butter and poppy seed to crackers.
In lightly greased casserole dish, layer chicken, soup mixture and crackers.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Put mixture in airtight container and keep refrigerated.
Makes about 20 ounces.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain the juice from all the cans of beans except pork and beans.
Combine all ingredients in a pan or roaster.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: louisiana doves
directions: Dust doves with seasoned flour (salt and pepper). Brown on all sides in cooking oil in heavy skillet. Add celery, onion and green pepper; saute for a few minutes. Add rice, tomatoes and bouillon to skillet. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Mix crackers, margarine and poppy seed.
Layer as follows in greased baking dish.
Put 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 of the soup mixture, 1/2 of the Ritz crackers, then all of the cheese.
Add another layer of chicken, then the soup mixture and crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued pork and beans
directions: Combine baked beans in tomato sauce (no pork) and 2 tablespoons chopped onion.
Place in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Trim fat off 4 to 5 ounces lean rib pork chops.
Season. Spread generously with prepared mustard and catsup.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and non-caloric liquid sweetener.
Place over beans. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Top each chop with 1 onion, sliced and 1 lemon slice. Secure with wooden pick.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: crusty sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and cook sweet potatoes; drain.
Add sugar, salt, 1/3 stick margarine, vanilla, milk and eggs.
Mix or mash and whip by hand and pour into casserole.
Top with topping of brown sugar, flour, margarine and chopped nuts.
Mix all together and spread over potato mixture.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown to make crunch topping.

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch and peanut butter.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated. Spread mixture into well buttered pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 11 x 2-inch cake pan with Pam.
Dump pineapple and pie filling into pan and mix together. Spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix over fruit mixture. Spread dry cake mix evenly.
Melt the stick of oleo and dribble over dry cake mix. Top with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be served hot or cold.
Very good topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine white chocolate, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts. Set aside.
Combine sugar, butter and sour cream in saucepan. Heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes while boiling.
Fold into chocolate mixture until smooth.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into pieces.
The smaller the pieces, the fewer calories.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add broccoli and onion to 5 cups hot water and boil 10 to 12 minutes.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir while cheese melts.
Add milks and margarine.
Stir and heat to boil.
Slowly add 1/2 cup cold water and flour.
Stir into hot mixture until thick.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil, oranges and 1/3 can pineapple.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Beat together.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake paper.
Fill with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned or cracked.
Cool slightly.
Put either strawberry or cherry topping on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Refrigerate.
Place almonds on top.
Place in red cabbage (acts as bowl).

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in saucepan; stir in water. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils; boil and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in milk and heat. DO NOT BOIL. Remove from heat; add vanilla. This can be kept warm in crock-pot. Serves 6.

title: aunt oleta's anniversary punch
directions: Mix juices in bowl, making sure sugar is dissolved.
Stir in scoops of strawberry ice cream.
Just before serving, slowly add ginger ale.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form dough into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cook for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fridge pickles
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed to a boil.
Cool. When liquid is cool, pour over cucumbers, onions and peppers. Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Place mixture into pint jars with tight fitting lids.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 5 pints.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Cook mixture until thickened and set to cool.
Add 3 well beaten egg whites.
Mix until blended and put on pie.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix powdered milk and sugar; set aside.
Into boiling water, add butter; stir until butter is melted.
Put into blender.
Add powdered milk and sugar mixture.
Blend for 2 or 3 minutes or until no sugar granules can be felt by fingers.
Yields 1 1/4 cups (same as a can).
Refrigerate until cool.
Can be stored in refrigerator in sealed container for 1 week.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes on top of stove until tender.
Drain water. Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour can of cream of celery soup on top.
Spread, then place Velveeta cheese on top and bake at 250° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven

sugar.

eggs,
