While cake is still warm, pour the other half can of syrup over the cake and let it seep down.

title: oven baked caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn; place in large oven roasting pan.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add baking soda; mix well.
Pour mixture over popcorn, mixing well to coat evenly.
Bake for 50 minutes at 250°; stir every 10 minutes.
Cool on wax paper covered counter.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Save 3/4 cup of this mixture for top crumbs.
To the remainder, add baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, egg and sour milk; beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into an 8-inch square, oiled pan and scatter reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients and pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake. Mix pineapple and sugar and flour for topping.
Bring to a good boil.
Pierce cake with fork while hot and pour over cake.
(This topping is bad to stick.)

title: french toast
directions: Butter both sides of each slice of bread.
Spread with applesauce or apple butter.
Beat one egg well.
Add milk.
Put bread which has been spread with butter and apple butter together as for a sandwich.
Cut in half.
Dip in egg mixture.
Brown on both sides.
Add more butter to skillet, if needed.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in an oiled loaf pan in a moderate oven about 350° until done.

title: fried yellow squash
directions: Dip squash slices in milk; dredge in flour.
Fry in 1/2 inch deep hot oil (375 degrees) until light, golden brown, turning once.
Drain.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in water until water evaporates. Add other ingredients; simmer until flavors blend.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Brown ground meat; drain and set aside.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with beef; top with cheese, onions and chilies.
Pour remaining batter over top.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in 2 quarts water.
Mix and add pineapple juice, sugar, and 7-Up. Add sherbet just before serving.
(Can substitute strawberry Jell-O and Kool-Aid.)

title: cinnamon-nut coffee cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, vanilla pudding mix, eggs, oil and water together.
Mix brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon together.
Swirl approximately half of mixture into cake mixture.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top of cake.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes, or until top is firm and light golden brown.
Bake in a large, 3-quart,
9 x 13-inch casserole dish that has been lightly greased with Crisco and lightly floured.

title: no-sugar fruit salad(diabetic)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple in saucepan.
Stir a small amount of juice into cornstarch and return to saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Stir in vanilla and sweetener.
(Dice chunks.)
Combine pineapple and equal amount of banana slices.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Toss until well coated.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: glazed apple pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and dredge in flour.
Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown chops on both sides.
Remove from skillet and drain all except 1 tablespoon of grease.
Return chops to skillet and top with apples, brown sugar and maple syrup.
Cover and simmer for 35 minutes.

title: polly's spinach pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook in salted water for 7 minutes.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Place in covered dish to marinate.

title: yummy frozen cherry salad
directions: Combine condensed milk and pineapple.
Stir in nuts and pie filling.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. May use as a salad or dessert.
(Variation: Use peach or blueberry pie filling.)

title: orange relish
directions: Remove the thin peel from 1/2 orange; reserve.
Remove peel from all oranges and discard.
Quarter oranges in food processor along with reserved peel, carrots, green pepper and onion. Process until coarse.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Cover and chill in refrigerator (several hours before serving).

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Beat in the chocolate mixture while still warm.
Refrigerate 10 minutes to cool.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour into crumb crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: chocolate lava
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and the 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Then add milk, vanilla, melted butter and the nuts.
Put this mixture in a greased 9 x 13 pan or a casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar and the 1/2 cup cocoa and sprinkle on the top of the mixture.
Pour boiling water over the entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with vanilla or coffee ice cream or whipped cream.

title: three layer bars
directions: In a double boiler, heat margarine, sugar, cocoa and vanilla until smooth.
Add slightly beaten egg and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and mix in graham cracker crumbs and coconut. Pat mixture firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: A fun holiday activity for kids and their parents.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: In a large skillet, lightly brown onion, green pepper, beef and rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain whole kernel corn. Lightly beat egg and add all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: broccoli with lemon and garlic
directions: Place steamer rack in bottom of saucepan.
Add enough water to come almost to bottom of rack.
Place over medium heat.
When water boils add broccoli; cover saucepan.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Combine all but Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Mix well.
Place cooked broccoli in serving bowl. Drizzle with garlic mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and freshly ground black pepper to taste.

title: grits casserole
directions: Prepare grits as directed on package, except omit salt.
Add Cheez Whiz and oleo, stirring until melted.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return to hot mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High 9 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: dump soup
directions: Dump all the ingredients into a large pot and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ham steak-rice stuffing
directions: Cover seedless raisins with boiling water and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine raisins, cooked rice, frozen orange juice, pepper, nutmeg and beaten egg.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Cook broccoli; set aside.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with
Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat.
Pour over remaining ingredients that have been combined.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: pink lemonade icebox pie
directions: Set out pink lemonade until softened to room temperature.
Mix in large bowl softened pink lemonade and Cool Whip; mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie crust; place in top of refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Measure orange and pineapple juice.
Add water to make 3 1/2 cups.
Heat to boiling; dissolve jello.
Cool.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken, then stir in orange juice (partially thawed).
Chill until thickening.
Stir in fruit.
Chill until jello sets.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt just until blended.
Add walnuts.
Put in 2 (9 x 5-inch) bread pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes before removing.

title: apricot foldovers
directions: Combine cottage cheese, margarine and flour.
Make little balls and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out each ball.
Put 1 teaspoon apricot preserves on one half of rolled out dough and fold over.
Dip filled foldover in beaten egg white and then in walnut-sugar mixture.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cold noodle salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles and set aside.

Mix together and heat salad oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, Accent, pepper, garlic powder and prepared mustard. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly and remove from heat. Pour mixture over noodles and mix together.
Chop onion and pimentos and add to noodles.
Slice cucumber and add to noodles. Add parsley flakes to noodles.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate 48 hours.
Toss several times to keep noodles from sticking together.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Thaw and soften dough.
Cut 16 slashes across loaf 1/2-inch apart, almost to bottom of dough.
Combine cherries, extract and nuts.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of mixture for topping.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of mixture into each cut.
Press loaf together and place in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Cover pan; let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack before trying to slice it.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to rolling boil in large saucepan.
Add peanut butter and stir until dissolved.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread and press, then cut.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients, then add sugar and flour together before adding to the liquid mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake on 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 1 pie.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in a large bowl; let stand 1 hour. Add
brown
sugar
and
egg;
mix
well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into oat mixture. Stir
in oil,
lemon
rind
and raisins (if used).
Spoon into greased muffin
pans,
filling
1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Yields about 18 muffins.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a large casserole dish for 1 hour at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Let cool. Pull off bone. Place chicken in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream together and spread over chicken. Crumble Ritz crackers and spread over soup mixture. Spread pieces of butter over crackers. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: wine potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pare and slice potatoes; arrange half the slices in a greased casserole.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 of the onion over the potatoes. Spoon 1/2 of the soup over top, then pour 1/2 of the wine over the soup.
Repeat layers; cover casserole.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fried onion mum
directions: Make batter by mixing cornstarch, flour, garlic, salt, paprika, salt and pepper until well-blended.
Stir in beer.
Mix well; set aside.
Heat oil in a deep-fryer to 375° to 400°.
Meanwhile, cut about 3/4-inch off top of each onion and remove skin.
Slicing vertically through the top of each onion to about 1/2-inch from base.
Divide each onion into quarter sections.
Do not cut through base.
Slice each quarter section vertically four more times. Gently spread the slices apart to form petals.
Remove some petals at the center of flower to make room for dipping sauce.
Dip the cut onion into seasoned flour, shaking afterward to remove any excess.
Mix reserved beer batter again to blend ingredients. Separate the floured petals and dip onion into beer batter to coat petals.
When oil in deep fryer is at 375° to 400°, gently lower the batter-coated onion into the fryer basket.
Deep fry for 1 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn onion and continue frying to brown other side.
Remove to drain on paper towels.
Place the fried onion upright in a shallow bowl.
Serve hot with Creamy Chili Sauce in center of onion.
Repeat procedure with remaining onions. Makes 6 servings of 1 onion each.

title: grandma fisher's butterscotch pie
directions: Brown the brown sugar, butter and water in an iron skillet until it makes a thread in a spoonful of the following milk mixture.
Mix egg yolks, white sugar, flour and milk together; mix well.
Add to brown sugar mixture.
Cook until thick.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter into a 2-quart baking dish; set aside. Drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Bring peaches and juice just to a boil; set aside.
Mix in bowl 1 cup sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Pour over butter in dish. Spoon hot peaches over batter.
Sprinkle remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Best when served warm.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: oven fried chicken parmesan
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir well.
Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, paprika and salt.
Stir.
Dip each piece of chicken in egg mixture, then dredge in flour mixture, coating well.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix next five ingredients together in saucepan and bring to boil; pour over beans.
Refrigerate overnight and add rest of ingredients.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tight container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix. Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain.
Melt margarine. Add flour and mix.
Add to macaroni along with cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour macaroni mixture into well-greased glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon party loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bone.
Combine with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and salt.
Chill several hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Peel potatoes and eggs.
Dice potatoes and eggs.
Chop onion.
Dice celery; mix together with 1/2 of Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar and water a few minutes, then add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts smell parched or pop (will cook more due to hot syrup).
Then add soda.
Beat vigorously and pour in greased marble.

title: fat burning soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on high for 5 minutes. Then cook on medium until desired tenderness.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir twice.
Add shrimp and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a huge dishpan or other container.
Combine syrup, cream and sugar in large saucepan; cook until soft ball forms in cold water.
Pour cooked mixture over dry ingredients and mix well to coat.
Divide into greased pans, about three, 9 x 13-inch.
Using paper lining from cereal boxes, press the candy firmly into pans with your hands.

title: olive dip
directions: Place nuts in processing bowl of a food processor.
Grind until the nuts are finely chopped.
Transfer to mixing bowl. Place the drained olives in the food processor; grind.
Put the olives on top of the nuts in mixing bowl.
Place cream cheese and mayonnaise in food processor; blend well.
While processor is running, add olive juice and blend well.
Add cream cheese mixture to nuts and olives.
Stir to blend.
Refrigerate until served. Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scoop inside pulp from tomatoes and turn upside down to drain. Fry onion to light brown in butter, add pulp and meat.
Cook until almost all water is out of tomatoes.
Squeeze out all surplus milk in bread and measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add this to meat mixture, add egg and garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and basil leaf. Mix all ingredients well and cook until almost dry.
Stuff tomato shells with this dressing and sprinkle top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; lay out in casserole dish.
Pour can of mushroom soup on top. Mix with water to make soupy.
Lay sliced potatoes on top, then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Bake covered, then for 10 minutes, uncovered, to brown.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in apples. Mix well and let stand 10 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Process 5 pounds pressure for 8 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in lightly salted, boiling water until tender. Melt butter; add onion and cook until tender.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and ginger in small pan.
Gradually add orange juice. Cook on low heat until thickened and smooth.
Place carrots in casserole dish.
Place onion on top and pour sauce over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Mix salt and pepper into flour.
Beat eggs and milk in a bowl. Dip meat into liquid mix, then flour, pressing firmly with hands. Dip into liquid again and flour again.
Fry in hot oil, about 3-inches deep, until floats and is brown.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Place chuck roast on a large sheet of aluminum foil. Spread A-1 sauce to cover roast. Spread onion soup mix and mushroom soup over A-1 sauce, covering roast well. Wrap carefully to seal aluminum foil around roast. Bake in pan or baking dish at 350° for about 4 hours. Makes wonderful gravy with roast.

title: mississippi mud sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Serve warm.
Delicious over ice cream or sliced pound cake or both!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Top with 1 cup grated cheese, 1 1/2 cup crushed potato chips, 3/4 cups chopped toasted almonds.
bake for 45 min. at 400°.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl (except for corn flakes and margarine).
Grease 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan and spread mixture in it.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Saute pepper and onion in 1/2 stick butter.
Mash squash.
Add to mushroom and chicken soup.
Add beaten eggs and sauteed peppers and onions.
Mix well; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 stick butter with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle a thick layer of crumbs over casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: shell macaroni tuna salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Combine shells, vegetables and tuna.
Mix well. Stir together mayonnaise and sour cream or salad dressing.
Add to macaroni mixture.
Mix well.

title: hillary clinton's cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Beat together the shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Allow cookies to "set" for 2 minutes before placing them on wire racks to cool.
Yield:
7 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken country captain wisconsin style
directions: Dredge chicken in flour which has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings until soft.
Add curry; cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, thyme and currants; cook 3 more minutes.
Place chicken in baking dish. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with toasted almonds.

title: steamed sea bass
directions: Score fish diagonally several times, almost to the bone. Place on a steamer deep enough to contain all the juices.
Press ginger and mushroom strips into the fish crevices.
Dribble soy sauce over along with oil, pepper and sherry.
Cook for 10 minutes in a steamer with a porous lid, bamboo or perforated metal. Sprinkle with chopped onions.
Any leftover liquid makes a lovely stock base.
Serves 2.
Cannot be frozen.

title: deer barbecue
directions: Simmer together tomato soup, pepper and onion for 5 minutes in skillet.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on hot buns.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
In a bowl, mix flour, salt, black pepper and 2 teaspoons thyme and set aside.
In another bowl, mix milk, egg and whites and Tabasco sauce; set aside.
In third bowl, mix bread crumbs, pepper, paprika and thyme.
Roll chicken in flour; dip in egg wash and roll in bread crumb mixture. Place on waxed paper; cover with wrap and sit in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake on a rack.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers on bottom and sides.
Do not crush the graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk together.
When mixed, fold into the Cool Whip.
When the filling is finished, pour over the graham crackers.
Then line the top of the pan with whole graham crackers.
Cut the sides so they are even.

title: fruit squares
directions: Combine flour, sugar
and baking powder in a bowl.
Cut butter into this after mixture is crumbly.
Quickly mix in egg with fork. Put 1/2 of mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch pan, then put pie filling
over
this,
then put rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: kahlua-pecan bake
directions: Remove rind from top of cheese, cutting to within 1/2 inch of outside edges.
Place on an oven-safe dish.
Combine pecans, Kahlua and brown sugar.
Spread over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for
3 to 5 minutes or just until soft.
Serve immediately with apple slices or gingersnaps.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cook at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: golden carrot bake
directions: In saucepan, combine carrot, water, rice and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 25 minutes.
Do not drain.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese, milk, eggs, onion and pepper. Turn carrot-rice mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Top with remaining cheese. Return to oven about 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sandwich filling #3
directions: Mix equal parts of raisins, carrot and peanuts with mayonnaise and juice.
(It takes quite a lot of mayonnaise to keep it from being dry.)

title: carrot salad
directions: Toss the shredded carrots with the mayonnaise and sugar.
Stir in the raisins and serve.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of roasting pan with broccoli.
Place cutlets on top of broccoli in a single layer.
In a mixing bowl, mix cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over top of cutlets and spread evenly.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of soup mixture and sprinkle bread crumbs over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients then add egg, flour and baking soda.
Add chunk chocolates, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon and beet salad
directions: Prepare 3 hours before serving or one day ahead.
In medium bowl, toss 1 teaspoon of grated lemon peel with remaining ingredients until well combined.
Refrigerate at least 2 1/2 hours to blend flavors.
Garnish salad with remaining 1 teaspoon lemon peel before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Tear into small pieces and put in the bottom of a baking dish.
Drain 2 cans of vegetables and pour over chicken.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup and a little of the stock where you cooked the chicken in a bowl, mix well and pour over vegetables.
Beat margarine, milk and flour until smooth. Pour over the soup and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tuna mold
directions: Heat tomato soup slightly.
Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Place in mold. Refrigerate overnight to set.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix cornstarch, baking powder, pepper, flour and salt.
Mix water and egg together; add to dry mixture.
Dip the onion rings or mushrooms in the batter, covering completely.
The onions or mushrooms will look like there isn't enough batter on them, but the batter will puff up as cooked.
Fry in half inch of oil.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cereal. Blend milk, egg and bananas.
Add shortening.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until all flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Chill overnight. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and box of jello.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add to mixture.
Stir well.
Add marshmallows. Refrigerate and serve.

title: m&m's hot chocolate
directions: Place candies, molasses and ginger in blender container.
Add hot milk.
Cover container and whip until smooth.
Pour into warm glasses or mugs.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields 2 cups.

title: hummus sandwich spread or dip
directions: Drain garbanzos, reserving 1/4 cup liquid, and set aside. Process all ingredients in food processor or mash thoroughly in medium size bowl.
Serve on pitas, tortillas, bread or crackers; with tomatoes, lettuce, sprouts, salsa, yogurt or sour cream.

title: gooey cakes
directions: Mix ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: candied onions
directions: Cover onions with hot salted water; cook about 15 minutes and drain.
Put in skillet with oleo, sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes until glazed and golden brown.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Alternately add flour mixture
and milk.
Add bananas, pecans, nutmeg and vanilla. Grease
and
lightly flour pans.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes. Makes 2 loaves in 4 x 8 x 3-inch pans.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in butter.
Stir in morsels and chopped walnuts.
Pour into shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: lisa's calico beans
directions: Fry bacon; then crumble.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat. Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350° uncovered. (Do not drain liquid from beans.)

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix together real good and let sit for 24 hours in refrigerator before eating.
(Will only keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.)

title: diet soup
directions: Chop vegetables; combine all ingredients in large kettle, cover and simmer at least 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Makes about 3 quarts of soup, about 30 calories per cup.

title: valentine punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in blender.
Add cranberry juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale, 7-Up or Sprite.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together to make sauce.
Pour over the frozen hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine
first
ingredients;
set aside.
In another bowl, combine
eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients;
stir in the apples and the nuts. Bake at 350° in
greased
muffin
tins
for 35 to 40 minutes. Yields 24 to 36 mini-muffins or 18 large muffins.

title: chicken mushroom with wine sauce
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for the first 45 minutes.
Double recipe for 2 cut up chickens.

title: red river guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and mash.
Then add rest of the ingredients and mix together.
It is a very good garnish for spicy tacos or as dip for your favorite chips.

title: hot water sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches or 9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Beat eggs in small mixing bowl on high speed for 5 minutes; pour into large mixer bowl.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat in water, vanilla and lemon extract on low speed.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt on low speed; continue beating until batter is smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake until top springs back when touched lightly in center, 25 to 30 minutes; cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, according to directions on cake mix box.
Cool in pan.
When cool, punch holes in top of cake and cover with mixture of Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
After mixture is absorbed into cake, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle generously with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, onion and salt.
Blend soup and milk.
Heat; add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture. Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: italian chicken breast
directions: In medium bowl, combine cheeses, 2 cups of flour, parsley and dressing mix.
Mix well.
In shallow bowl, whisk together milk and eggs.
Put remaining flour in a separate shallow bowl.
Coat chicken with flour, dip into milk mixure, then into cheese mixture, coating evenly and pressing into chicken.
Heat about 1/4 inch oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 5-6 minutes on each side, or until cooked through.
Garnish with parmesan and parsley.

title: beans 'n weiners biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice weiners in rounds and combine in saucepan with beans, catsup, onions and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon hot mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Arrange biscuits over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and no longer doughy.

title: mary's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water. Scald the milk and set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Put sugar and oil in a large mixing bowl. Add the milk and mix well.

Add the yeast mixture and the cold water. Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough. Pour onto a floured board and knead until easy to handle, place into a greased bowl and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.

Take out and knead again, then pinch off a little dough at a time and make into rolls, put into a greased 12 or 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet pan, let rise for about 1 hour and bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: french apple pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients except butter.
Pour ingredients in pie shell and dot with butter, then cover with top crust.
Make slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with vanilla ice cream.
